title: texas pie
directions: Melt margarine and combine with flour and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13 pan; bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine powdered sugar and cream cheese; fold in 2 cups whipped topping. Spread over cooled crust.
Let cool in refrigerator for 10 minutes. Mix chocolate and vanilla puddings with milk; add vanilla.
Pour over cooled cream layer; let cool in refrigerator for 10 minutes. Spread 2 cups whipped topping over all.
Top with 1/2 shaved Hershey bar.
Let cool at least 30 minutes in refrigerator before serving.

title: snausages
directions: Slice sausages into 3/4-inch slices.
Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low 4 plus hours, stirring occasionally.

title: cheesy spaghetti bake
directions: Brown chuck and onion in frying pan.
Drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Break spaghetti into thirds. Cook according to package directions.
Rinse and drain.
Mix spaghetti and sauce.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt.
Slowly add Carnation and water.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly until thickened.
Add 1/2 cup American cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Stir until melted.
Spread 1/2 spaghetti mixture in bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon all of cheese sauce over spaghetti.
Top with remaining spaghetti mixture and remaining 1/2 cup American cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Wash and core pears.
Grind or put in blender.
Combine with other ingredients in a heavy kettle and stir until sugar is dissolved over medium heat.
Cook, stirring frequently over lowered heat until of good spreading consistency.
Ladle into sterilized jars. Seal.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour and milk in a double boiler until thick; then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into cooked crust.
Top with meringue made of 3 beaten egg whites with a teaspoon of sugar gradually added as whites are beaten.
Do not add sugar too soon to meringue.
Make sure whites are well beaten before adding sugar.
Bake at 350° until meringue is browned.

title: rice stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice the tops from the tomatoes. Scoop out the pulp.
Do not break the skin.
Mix the rice together with seasonings, tomato pulp, lemon juice and oil.
Fill the tomato shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes.

title: wendy's chili(clone)
directions: Brown ground round in oil; drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat and serve.

title: squash with chili peppers
directions: Mix cooked squash, Cheez Whiz and chilies.
Crunch up chips and add to mixture.
Save some chips for the top.
Sprinkle reserved chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apricot delight
directions: Combine jello, sugar and water in small saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit; set aside to cool.
Combine condensed milk and cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Stir in gelatin mixture, then nuts; pour into a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Easy and good as a salad or dessert; will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: pea-pickin' cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat in separate skillet.
Brown onion in hot fat.
Stir in flour, then stir in other ingredients and cook, stirring until medium thickness.

title: lemon lime salad
directions: Stir lemon and lime jello into hot water until dissolved well. Stir in remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into rectangular dish and chill for several hours prior to serving. Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break up buns and add all ingredients. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a skillet.
Make a batter of the remaining ingredients and pour over cake filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat first 6 ingredients until fluffy.
At low speed, beat in next 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Immediately press nuts or candies into cookies or press with thumb and fill with jam. Cool; store in airtight container.
Makes 6 dozen.
Can be baked up to one week ahead.

title: charlie's blintzes
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese, yolks and sugar together.
Remove crust from bread and roll bread slices very thin.
Spread cream cheese mixture over bread slices (thick like peanut butter on a sandwich).
Roll up in jelly roll fashion.
Melt butter and margarine together.
Dip blintzes in melted butter.
Freeze at least 2 hours or overnight.
Cut on half and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, salt and sugar.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch shallow pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: creamed cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, about 1 minute, until creamy.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and cover saucepan with lid; cheese will melt.
Serve with cooked cauliflower.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine seasonings, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip each chicken breast in egg, then roll in bread crumb mixture, coating evenly.
Place chicken in a lightly buttered baking pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then turn chicken over and bake 15 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Spoon tomato sauce over chicken and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Make Dream Whip using 2 packages of Dream Whip and 1 cup milk. Add the vanilla.
Beat 6 minutes until stiff peaks form.
Add instant pudding and 1 3/4 cups milk.
Beat an additional 2 minutes.
Turn into a 9 5/8-inch deep crust.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with mini morsels.

title: lizzies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix the 3 cups of
flour
with
soda and spices. Sprinkle flour on mixed fruit. Add flour
mixture to first mixture with milk and whiskey. Add fruit mixture.	Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach sandwiches
directions: Mix spinach, seasoning, cheese, bacon and mayonnaise together. Spread on bread; cut off crust and into finger size sandwiches (3 servings to 1 sandwich).

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Combine water, bouillon cubes, broccoli, vegetables, potatoes and onion in large kettle.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Then add soup and milk.
Mix and heat through.
Add cheese.
Turn off heat and stir until melted.
Add pepper to taste.
Makes 6 quarts.
Freezes well.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla and bananas together with a potato masher.
Mix until smooth.
Mix in flour, milk and nuts. Beat or mash vigorously.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Prepare pudding with 3 cups of milk.
Fold in whipped cream. In 9 x 12-inch dish, layer with graham crackers and pudding; final layer should be graham crackers.
Spread frosting on top. Refrigerate several hours.

title: crispy onion rings
directions: Peel and slice onions about 1/3-inch thick; separate into rings.
Pour buttermilk into large shallow pan.
Add onion rings and soak for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, except oil for frying, in a bowl and stir until smooth.
Heat frying oil on medium-high heat.
Remove onion rings from buttermilk and dip into batter.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain rings on paper towels.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: betty powers' layered salad
directions: Take mayonnaise and sugar and mix well.
Spread over the top of salad and do not leave any air holes.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, crumble some crisp cooked bacon over the top.
Slice the hard-boiled eggs and place along the edge. Tomatoes, cut in wedges, can be placed on top for decoration.
You can also add cauliflower or broccoli to the salad.
Do not use anything that will get mushy.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown hash in oil.
Add seasonings; cook for 3 minutes.
Add eggs. Cook until eggs are almost done.
Mix in salsa and cook 2 minutes.
Serve on warm flour tortillas.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook until desired thickness over medium heat.

title: fantastic fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Combine all ingredients and enjoy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam Broccoli and cook rice.
Add everything together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350 until light brown approximately 10 minutes.

title: stir-fry cashew chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in salt, wine, cornstarch, soy sauce and water for 20 minutes.
Heat oil in wok or frying pan.
Stir-fry chicken for several minutes.
Move aside and add vegetables. Stir-fry until desired tenderness.
Toss together with cashews. Cook until chicken is done.
Serve over Ramen noodles.

title: apple
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour.
Cook until thick.
Add margarine; let cool.
Add diced apples one at a time.
Pour into dish.
Put Cool Whip on top.
May cut up cherries on top.
Place in refrigerator.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: peanut-butter bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, butter or margarine and vanilla in a large bowl; beat until well blended.
Beat in brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour and salt just until well blended.
Spread batter in a greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 35 minutes or until the center springs back when lightly touched with fingertip. Remove pan from oven to wire rack; cool slightly.

title: the "secret" recipe for orange julius
directions: Put orange juice in blender.
Fill with ice to 3/4 full.
Add water to just cover ice.
Add syrup and "secret powder" (i.e. instant vanilla pudding mix; use a good brand).
Blend until smooth.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: greek meatballs
directions: Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice in large pan; heat slowly.
Make meatballs of desired size from the first 4 ingredients.
Drop gently into boiling sauce.
Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pink grapefruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water; let stand 5 to 7 minutes; stir.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water and stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold or flat baking dish.
Serves 8. (Two times this recipe in 9 x 12-inch baker equals 15 servings.) This makes a nice fruit accompaniment for brunch.

title: diabetic apple dessert
directions: Melt butter; add vanilla, cinnamon, Splenda and pie filling. Pour 1/2 of mixture in baking dish. Cut biscuits in 4 pieces each. Place pointed end up in dish on top of mixture. Pour other half over biscuits. Sprinkle pecans on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are done and brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Drain clams, reserving 3/4 c. liquid.
In skillet, slowly heat oil and butter.
Add garlic and saute until golden.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the clam liquid, chopped parsley and salt; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add clams, simmer 3 minutes.
Makes enough for 8 oz. of spaghetti.

title: grandma's toasted cookies
directions: Can add as desired!
Cut up nuts or cut up cherries.
Can use anise flavoring, lemon flavoring, vanilla flavoring, almonds and almond flavoring.
Can also use 3 tablespoons of cocoa. Can make 5 different kinds

title: peach and raspberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium bowl, combine peaches, 1 cup sugar, orange peel and vanilla, tossing to combine.
Butter 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place peach mixture in baking dish. Sprinkle the raspberries and mint through the peaches.
Place baking dish in oven for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese bake
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar, flour and cheese.
Put in casserole pan.
Pour crackers on top.
Pour melted butter on top. Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: cherry chiffon pie
directions: Use graham crackers or cookies for crust.
Mix and pour. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: birthday pound cake
directions: Mix margarine and Crisco; add sugar and 1 egg at a time. Mix flour and baking powder together and add this to mixture. Alternate with milk. Add flavoring and beat until smooth. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: Puree undrained tomatoes in blender.
In hot oil, in large saucepan, saute onion and garlic until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Add pureed tomatoes, tomato paste, 1 1/2 cups water, parsley, salt, sugar, oregano, basil and pepper.
Mix well. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 1 hour.

title: finger sandwiches
directions: Cut crust off white or wheat bread and spread mixture to make sandwiches.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cut up the broccoli, onion, cucumber, celery and tomatoes fine.
Toss all ingredients with Italian dressing.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook for 1 1/2 minutes at a rolling boil.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain well and squeeze dry as possible.
Combine spinach with other ingredients.
Mix well and shape in marble size balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix vanilla cookies and powdered sugar.
Add bourbon, Karo and pecans.
Make into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Store in sealed jar for 10 days or longer.

title: low calorie creamy italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Whisk until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Yields 2/3 cup.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In casserole dish, alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over potato layers.
Cook, covered, at 350° until tender, about 45 minutes. Uncover the last 20 minutes.

title: hot brown
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk slowly, stirring as you add it.
Add shredded cheese and cook and stir until cheese has melted.
Toast bread.
Put first piece in small baking dish. Add ham, turkey and another piece of toast.
Pour cheese sauce over sandwich and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes. Take out and add a slice of tomato on the top with a couple pieces of bacon.

title: helen's banana nut bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well; set aside.
Combine sugar and shortening; cream until light and fluffy.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with bananas.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and arrange in ungreased glass baking dish. Next, mix the first 7 ingredients and let stand for 5 minutes. Add bread crumbs and mix well.
Place stuffing in each mushroom cap and drizzle the 1/2 stick melted butter over the top of them. Broil for 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: corn sticks
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Blend in milk.
Add shortening and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 500°. Grease small corn stick molds (5 x 1 1/2-inches) and set in oven until molds are hot.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all
ingredients together and use a spoon dipped in ice water to spoon into grease.
Deep fry.

title: opera creams
directions: Combine butter and cheese and cream well.
Add vanilla and sugar and knead with hands until well mixed.
Make balls and refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt wax and chocolate in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate and place on wax paper.
Keep refrigerated when set.

title: apple crunch
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Mix apples, 2/3 cup sugar, cinnamon and water.
Place this in bottom of baking dish.
Dot butter on top.
Mix softened stick of butter, flour and brown sugar with a fork.
Put on top of apples to form the crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: burritos
directions: Prepare ground beef and seasoning package according to package directions.
Warm tortillas according to package directions.
Divide meat mixture, beans and cheese among tortillas, leaving bottom 1/3 of tortilla plain.
Fold bottom of tortilla over meat mixture.
Fold 1 side toward center and roll up.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes, salsa and sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: caramel icing
directions: Put in iron skillet and bring to a boil.
Remove from stove and put in package of caramel bits. Beat well and put on cake.

title: peach cheesecake
directions: Mix pudding, flour, milk, baking powder, salt, margarine and egg together. Spray Pam or deep pie dish and place mixture on top. Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and reserved peach juice. Place peaches on top of crust mixture, then spread cream cheese mixture over top. Mix cinnamon and sugar. Sprinkle over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set in center. Serve warm.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Blend cornstarch and water.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Pat 3/4 of crumb mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in rhubarb mixture; sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: fudgemallow raisin candy
directions: Microwave chocolate and peanut butter in a 2 quart bowl on medium (50%) 2-3 minutes or until melted, stirring after each minute. Fold in marshmallows and raisins. Pour into foil lined 8 inch square pan. Chill until firm. Cut into squares.

title: cranberry gelatin mold
directions: Melt cranberry sauce in top of double boiler over hot water. Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients. Mold and chill.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain off fat.
Mix in casserole with the other ingredients.
Brown bread crumbs in margarine and garlic salt. Cover casserole with these bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy corn spread
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
In large bowl, crumble cheese with a fork or blend with mixer to form small bits.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except corn, until well blended.
Stir in corn.
Cover; chill several hours or overnight.
Can be stored in refrigerator up to 1 week.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Lightly steam vegetables (about 5 minutes for broccoli and asparagus, 1 minute for peas and squash).
Saute garlic in oil, carefully to not burn.
Add steamed vegetables and stir-fry briefly to blend flavors (vegetables should remain somewhat crisp).
Add tomatoes, parsley, basil and black pepper; heat through.

title: butterfinger tart
directions: Bake an angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together the butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and egg yolks until smooth. Whip the whipping cream and add to mixture.
Cut angel food cake in half.
Spread half of filling over cake and sprinkle 1/2 of chopped candy bars across it.
Put top half of cake back on and add the rest of the filling and candy bar chips on top.
Chill for several hours.

title: eggs in a whole
directions: Use a glass or anything round to cut a circle out of center of slice of bread.
Melt margarine in frypan.
Put bread and center cut out in hot butter.
Break and cut out in hot butter.
Break an egg into center of cut out bread slice.
Salt and pepper to taste. Don't break yellow of egg.
Brown on both sides.
May need to add more butter when flipping over.

title: judy's chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar and Crisco; beat in eggs until creamy.
Add milk and vanilla.
Combine other ingredients in other bowl.
Mix together until smooth and add 1/2 cup hot water.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream the margarine.
Add sugars and eggs; blend well.
Add dry ingredients.
Makes 4 dozen. Bake at 350°.

title: jack's rabbit stew
directions: Cut rabbit into pieces. Boil until tender.
Pull meat from bone.
Cut meat into small pieces (save water that rabbit was boiled in).
Cut carrots, celery and potatoes in small pieces. Put in a 5-quart boiler with water from rabbit.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Add chopped onion, tomato paste, tomatoes or juice, corn and peas to thicken juice in stew.
Make roux and add to stew or add instant potatoes, salt and pepper to taste.

title: raised biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Work in shortening with mixing fork.
Add all liquids, including dissolved yeast.

title: blueberry banana applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream margarine, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Alternately add dry ingredients, bananas and applesauce.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
You can put crushed corn flakes on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: calico meatball stew
directions: Mix beef, sausage, bread crumbs, oregano and egg.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
In 6-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, brown meatballs.
Spoon off fat.
Add gravy, tomatoes, potatoes, carrots, onion, bay leaf and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes. Stir in peas.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes more.
Remove bay leaf.

title: *butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then add vanilla.
To this mixture, add sifted dry ingredients and when blended well, add nuts.
Make in 2 rolls and chill.
Slice fairly thin and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat 10 minutes. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in a well-greased tube
pan.

title: spicy potato soup
directions: In a large pot, combine au gratin potatoes, corn, Ro-Tel and water. Mix well. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 to 18 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add milk, cheese and seasoning. Stir constantly until cheese is melted.

title: maple raisin crisps
directions: Combine oats and sugar.
Stir in oil, eggs and flavoring. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to oat mixture, blending well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/4 dozen.

title: cantonese pork chops
directions: Brown meat; add dressing.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Add pineapple chunks, snow peas and water chestnuts. Cover and simmer until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Add tomatoes and heat.	Arrange meat, fruit and vegetables on serving platter.
Thicken sauce, if desired.
Makes 6
servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
(I bring to a boil for 15 minutes, covered, then turn off the heat but do not remove from the burner.
Let stand on burner until cooled to warm and can be handled easily.
They will be tender, but not mushy.)
Peel and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add chopped onion, celery and pickles. Mix.
Add mayonnaise, mustard and pickle juice.
Mix.
If it seems to dry, add additional mayonnaise (or a little ranch dressing.) Salt and pepper to taste.
Add quartered boiled eggs, reserving one or two to slice on top.
Mix.
Top with sprinkle of paprika.

title: mom's lettuce and green onions
directions: Place chopped lettuce in a large serving bowl.
Place chopped onions on top. Heat bacon grease until it begins to smoke.
Pour over the onions. Sprinkle on salt and stir thoroughly. (Can omit salt if on a low sodium diet.)

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg whites and water until stiff.
Mix with pecans.
Mix other ingredients and then with pecans.
Place in shallow pan in 300° oven for 45 minutes.
Stir nuts every 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and put on wax paper.

title: greek stew
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in Dutch oven; add meat and coat with melted butter but do not brown.
Arrange sliced onions over meat.
Mix together tomato paste, wine, brown sugar, wine vinegar, garlic and then pour over meat.
Add bay leaf, cinnamon and cloves.
Cover kettle; simmer 3 hours or until meat is very tender.
Don't stir or turn!
Serve with potatoes, rice or noodles.
Kathy says this is a great dish to make when you're going to be busy.

title: german coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar with oil.
Add flour, sugar, salt and nutmeg. Mix well.
Add sour milk and eggs.
Add baking powder and baking soa; mix.
Pour into large greased cake pan.
Sprinkle topping on top of batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Gradually add sugar.
Cream well.
Beat until light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Gradually add flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: no sugar-low fat lemon cheesecake
directions: Spray 8-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie plate with non-stick cooking spray; sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; pour into blender.
Add cottage cheese and cream cheese, cover and blend at medium speed, scraping down sides occasionally.
Mix until completely smooth.
Pour in large bowl; stir in Cool Whip.
Pour in pans over graham cracker crumbs.
Chill until set, about 4 hours.

title: winter slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, orange zest and juice, salt and pepper.
Stir in cabbage, carrots, onion and fennel until well coated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix cookies and melted butter well.
Press into cake pan.
Top with softened ice cream.
Refrigerate.
Mix together powdered sugar, milk, butter and chocolate chips.
Cook 8 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Cool and pour over ice cream.
Freeze.
Press Spanish peanuts onto dessert.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Drain and put in casserole dish.
Add onion, cheese, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Add chestnuts and mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.
Mix cracker crumbs and butter; spread over vegetable mixture.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat and add flavoring.
Beat 2 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine until onion is clear.
Add tomatoes, chicken stock, green chilies, spices and chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer.
To serve, ladle soup over crushed tortillas and garnish with shredded cheese of your choice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and cinnamon in a bowl and set aside. Cream margarine and sugars; add egg. Add flour mixture a little at a time; add oatmeal, pecans and vanilla. Chill dough 1 hour. Make balls of dough. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Butter bottom of flat glass; dip in sugar and press dough ball flat. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fruit and nuts.
Gently fold in fruit and nuts last.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in small amount of fat.
Heat and bring other ingredients to a boil; add onion and hamburger and simmer 10 minutes.

title: banana cream topping
directions: Mash together bananas, sugar, and honey until smooth and strain through a sieve.
Fold banana mixture into whipped cream.
Or fold banana mixture into prepared topping using dessert topping mix. Makes 3 cups.

title: eggplant napoli
directions: In a skillet, saute chopped onion in oil.
Add tomato puree, water, salt, oregano, basil, marjoram and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
In a greased baking dish, alternate thin layers of sliced eggplant, tomato sauce and half of the grated cheese, starting with a layer of eggplant and ending with a layer of tomato sauce.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour. Minutes before removing from oven, sprinkle remaining grated cheese over top and continue heating until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: honey-glazed carrots
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add carrots.
Cover and heat to boiling; reduce heat. Boil until tender, 12 to 15 minutes; drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add garlic powder, ginger, orange peel, honey and orange juice.
Cook and stir over low heat 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add carrots to butter mixture. Toss gently to coat well. Makes 8 servings.

title: no fail pastry
directions: Sift directly into 9-inch pie plate the flour, salt and sugar. Mix oil and milk in a cup and pour over flour mixture.
Mix until moist.
Press to line pan and prick with fork.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Unlike most pastry, this can be handled as much as you need to and does not become tough.

title: tortellini with pink sauce
directions: Heat cream slowly on low heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Fold in tortellini.

title: smoke fish dip
directions: Remove skin and bones from fish.
Flake the fish.
Combine all the ingredients except chips.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving to blend flavors.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with chips.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: ham and cheese delights
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients for spread.
Cut open rolls and spread mix on each side.
Cut cheese slices into 4 parts and ham into 8 parts.
Place 2 ham squares and 1 cheese square between each roll. Return to pan and cover with foil.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° (longer if cold or frozen).
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: chickpea salad(serves 6)
directions: Combine the cooked chickpeas with the olive oil, vinegar, cumin, thyme and parsley.
Marinate for two hours.

title: seafood soup
directions: *You can use fresh shrimp.

title: chocolate peppermint pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pie crust according to package directions for one crust baked shell, using a 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 450° for 9 to 11 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool. Layer 2 cups ice cream over cooled pie crust.
Drizzle with fudge topping.
Top with remaining 2 cups ice cream.
Freeze overnight. Garnish with whipped cream and mint chocolate sandwich cookies. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Increase oven to 450°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When cool, drizzle with powdered sugar icing.

title: banana date muffins
directions: Combine bran and milk.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Add oil, honey, egg and mashed bananas.
Mix well.
Gradually add 1 cup flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir just enough to thoroughly mix. Place dates, raisins and nuts in a bowl.
Stir in the 1/4 cup flour to coat.
Stir fruit into batter.
Pour into well-greased muffin tins, filling two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes. Makes 24 regular.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine tea, fruit drink and sugar.
Chill until ready to serve.
Pour over ice ring in punch bowl or ice cubes in pitcher. Add ginger ale and garnishes just before serving.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: easy, easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, celery, almonds, salt, onion, lemon juice and mayonnaise together in a bowl.
Turn into a casserole.
Top with grated cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Soak spareribs in a mixture of shoyu, 1 teaspoon salt, ginger and cornstarch for 30 minutes.
Line shallow baking pan with foil. Spread ribs on pan and bake in a 425° to 450° oven until brown (15 minutes).

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Wash mushrooms; break off stems and put in bowl; set aside stems.
Rinse caps again and put on cookie sheet upside down or bottoms up.

title: reese's bars
directions: Crush graham crackers (in food processor).
Mix sugar, butter, graham crackers and 1 cup peanut butter.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: alaska shrimp quiche
directions: Beat together the eggs, half and half and seasoning.
Place mushrooms and shrimp in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle with cheese; add egg mixture and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is firm.
To prepare quiche ahead, bake 10 minutes less than directed; cool, then wrap and freeze.
When ready to use, unwrap and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: gram julia's cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press into 10-inch spring-form pan or pie plate.

title: apple nut coffee cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream sugar and shortening. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and sour cream alternately to creamed mixture.
Fold in apples, spread batter in prepared pan.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in water for 15 minutes.
Slice onion and cube the green pepper.
Mix all ingredients and add the drained hot carrots to the mixture.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
These improve when they are kept longer.

title: tuna bake
directions: Add water to soup.
Add tuna and 1/2 Chinese noodles (reserve the rest for topping).
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour in greased casserole, top with remaining Chinese noodles.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a casserole dish with butter. Sprinkle layer of bread crumbs.
Mix ingredients.
Layer with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hoagie dip
directions: Chop all ingredients into small pieces.
Combine in a bowl. Add mayonnaise (enough to make a spreadable consistency).
Add oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Serve with sliced Italian bread.

title: garlic grilled chicken(serves 4)
directions: Place each chicken breast between 2 pieces of plastic wrap. Flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thickness, using meat mallet or rolling pin.
Cut into 1-inch wide strips.
Place chicken in a shallow container.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour over chicken; cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Thread chicken onto skewers; cook over hot coals 6 to 8 minutes or until done, turning occasionally and basting with remaining marinade.
Serve with additional picante.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine the first seven ingredients.
Combine the corn, egg substitute, cheese, milk, onion, butter and jalapeno.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cut into squares; serve warm.
Makes 9 servings.

title: blueberry sour cream pudding
directions: Mix sour cream and sugar in a bowl, adding egg and blueberries. Stir in flour that has been sifted with salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown. Serve warm with hard sauce or milk seasoned with nutmeg, cinnamon, sugar and vanilla to taste.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and
sugar in a medium bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Stir in lemon peel and juice. Stir in 1 1/2 cups whipped topping. Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer, reserving several for garnish, if desired.
Pour 2 cups milk into a large bowl. Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute. Let stand 1 minute or until thickened. Gently stir in 1 cup of the whipped topping. Spoon over strawberries in crust. Refrigerate 4 hours.
Garnish with topping and strawberries. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: my spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for one hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: spinach bread with sausage
directions: Remove casing from sausages (or use sausage patties). Brown and crumble in frying pan.
Mix all ingredients (except for dough!) in a bowl. If mixture seems dry, add 1 to 2 tablespoons olive oil.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed and pour over nut mixture.

title: brownies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a small bowl.
Add nuts.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tex-mex layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip in a shallow pan (pizza pan).
Mix together avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Spread over bean dip. Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread over avocado mixture.
Chop onions and tomatoes.
Sprinkle onions, tomatoes, black olives and grated cheese on top.
Serve with chips.

title: eggless meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and make large patties.
Place in Pam sprayed skillet and brown on both sides. Cover.
Cook slowly until done.
Or bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hamburger-mushroom soup over rice
directions: While rice cooks, brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper in frypan.
When meat is brown, stir in the mushroom soup and heat through.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: halfway cookies
directions: Mix together all except chocolate bits, egg whites and 1 cup brown sugar
; spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread 1 package chocolate bits over this.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add brown sugar gradually.
Spread over the cookie mixture and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: yum yum yams
directions: Combine all
ingredients
except
yams
and
bring to a boil. Cook and
stir about 10 minutes until thick and syrupy. Pour over yams in
baking
dish
and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frosted strawberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice and set aside.
Prepare jello using only 3 cups water.
Stir in pineapple, strawberries and juice and marshmallows.
Pour mixture into serving bowl. Chill until firm.
Combine flour, sugar and salt in small saucepan.
Add reserved pineapple juice and butter.
Cook over medium heat until mixture reaches a boil and thickens.
Remove from heat and let cool completely.
Prepare whipped topping.
Fold in cooled juice mixture and coconut.
Spread mixture over chilled jello and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Makes approximately 15 servings.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix raisins, boiling water and baking soda together.
May cool and use immediately, or let stand overnight.
In morning, add remaining ingredients.
Put in well-greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 2 (8-inch) loaf pans.
Very good.

title: egg beater pot pie dough
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Mix Egg Beaters with water; then pour in flour mixture.
You can use some of this dough; put rest in ball and freeze up to 6 weeks.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool.

title: butter rich spritz cookies
directions: Sift together the flour and salt.
Cream the butter. Gradually add powdered sugar, creaming well.
Blend in eggs and extracts.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Mix thoroughly.
Press through cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with colored sugar or sprinkles before baking.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Rinse rice in hot water.
Mix with remaining ingredients, except raisins and butter.
Bake in greased casserole dish, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.
After the first hour, add raisins and butter, stirring well.
Serve warm or cold.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter; beat eggs in butter.
Add canned milk. Pour in mixed sugar and cocoa, then vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: parisian onion soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onions in butter until soft.
Blend in flour.
Add cream and milk; bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Season to taste.
Put toast in a tureen.
Pour soup over toast and sprinkle with some cheese.
Grate some pepper over the top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hodgepodge salad
directions: Halve or quarter large potatoes.
In a 3-quart saucepan cook potatoes in 3 cups boiling salted water for 12 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and ham; return to boiling.
Add cabbage. Cover and simmer for 3 minutes more or until cabbage is crisp-tender.
Drain.
Stir in dressing.
Cool slightly.

title: foundation refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk and water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening and allow to cool.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add yeast, dissolved in water, and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Place in well-greased bowl and sit in warm place to rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and shape rolls.
Place in a greased pan and allow to rise.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush with melted butter when done.
Dough can be placed in refrigerator when mixed and stored until ready to use.
Then shape into rolls and let rise.
Bake as directed.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Pound each breast very thin with smooth meat hammer or rolling pin; do not tear flesh.
Place 1 1/2 tablespoons butter in center of each breast.
Combine chives, salt and pepper; sprinkle over butter.
Roll each breast and overlap sides so butter mixture is completely enclosed.
Beat egg and milk together.
Roll chicken in cracker crumbs, then in egg and again in cracker crumbs; coat well.
Refrigerate at least 20 minutes.
Deep fry chicken in oil at 375° until well browned, about 8 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large heavy saucepan and bring to a boil on high heat about 4 minutes.
Adjust heat so mixture bubbles gently, and simmer, partly covered, for 40 minutes or until the barley is tender.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Add other ingredients.
Chill and serve with mayonnaise to which yolks of 2 hard-boiled eggs have been added.

title: brown eyed susan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts.
Roll into balls. Place on cookie sheet and press down in middle with your thumb. Bake at 325° until light brown.
Cool and fill with your choice of frosting.
Top with nuts.

title: mandarin orange upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Heat 1/2 c.
butter in 9x13 pan, in oven until melted.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Arrange orange segments over brown sugar. Sprinkle with coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Stir pecans into batter.
Pour carefully into pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in center.
Immediately turn upside down onto heat proof serving platter. Leave pan over cake 1 minute.
Cool completely.

title: christine maass' chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix ingredients together in a casserole dish. Top with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
If desired, add broccoli tops and/or favorite chopped veggies.

title: quick oven potatoes
directions: Melt 1/2 of the oleo in a baking dish or pan.
Pour in potatoes, onion and seasoning.
Top with rest of oleo and mushroom soup.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in a 325° oven.
Stir. Return to oven for 15 minutes more.
Stir again; top with cheese. Bake 10 minutes more.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound chicken.
Spread with butter and set aside.
Blend 3/4 cup butter, parsley, thyme and marjoram in saucepan.
Slice cheese thin.
Place in center of breasts, add ham; roll.
Coat in flour, then egg, then bread crumbs.
Arrange in well buttered dish.
Melt butter mixture and spoon over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes.
Pour wine over chicken and bake 15 more minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together butter, oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Beat well.
Add zucchini and nuts (if desired).
Bake at 350° in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: crispy rice cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets.
Cream margarine and sugar and vanilla with mixer until fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Use wooden spoon to stir in cereal.
Use 1 tablespoon dough for each cookie leaving space between each.
Bake until lightly browned, about 8 minutes.
Rotate pan if cookies bake unevenly.
Transfer to cooling rack with metal spatula.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Cook ingredients for 20 minutes. Add 2 small boxes of wild strawberry Jell-O or 1 large box; stir well.
Pour into jars, seal and refrigerate.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and put in baking dish.
Make sauce of bean juice, margarine and flour.
Stirring over low heat, add cheese.
Set aside.
Add Beau Monde seasoning, garlic salt and salt and pepper to drained beans.
Stir well.
Then pour sauce over beans.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli salad ii
directions: Wash and drain broccoli well. Cut into flowerettes and tender stems. Do not add salt. Mix broccoli with other ingredients and chill. May add some chopped onions if desired.

title: scalloped potatoes and chops
directions: In a skillet, blend flour into melted margarine and add milk, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Add salt, pepper, mustard and onion.
Stir and set aside.
Season chops with salt and pepper to taste.
Broil chops until slightly browned.
Place in single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place half of the potatoes over chops and cover with half the sauce.
Add remaining potatoes and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake until top is browned (about 5 minutes).

title: hot dog bites
directions: Combine all ingredients, except hot dogs, in slow cooker.
Mix well.
Cover and heat on low for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Add hot dogs and heat for 1 hour.

title: beans and pita
directions: Mix refried beans and tomatoes.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, oregano and basil to taste.
Let simmer in broiler for approximately 10 minutes.
Place mixture and cheese in pita bread. Bake in oven for 10 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: finnish chocolate ice
directions: Melt chocolate with butter in top of double boiler; cool slightly. Beat egg in a small bowl with an electric mixer.
Slowly add chocolate and orange peel.
Drop from teaspoon onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Yield: 48 pieces.

title: summertime fruit salad
directions: In a large pan, boil water and sugar for 10 minutes. Add pineapple, bananas and cherries. Set aside and cool. In a bowl, mix orange juice and water; place in freezer and chill, but do not freeze. Remove and mix in fruit mixture. Freeze.

title: wilted spinach
directions: Cut bacon in half-inch lengths with scissors and saute with the onion for 10 minutes.
Lift out bacon to crisp; blend flour into fat remaining in pan.
Add liquids gradually and cook over low heat until thickened.
Add seasonings, then the spinach and celery.
Toss lightly until vegetables are coated with the dressing and stand over low heat until just warm.
Sprinkle crumbled crisp bacon over the top.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa together.
Add sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla and flour.
Mix until all flour is moistened.
Add nuts and mix.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: puffy fish patties
directions: Heat oil in frying pan. Mix all ingredients together except flour. Scoop by spoonful. Press into patties and dredge in flour. Fry in skillet to golden brown. Drain on paper towel. Serves 6.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and 3/4 cup sugar.
Stir in milk and melted margarine.	Spread in 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with mixture
of
cup sugar and cocoa.
Pour hot water over this. Bake
inside 12-inch Dutch oven on small rocks to raise for 1 hour.
Use	15
coals
on top and 8 coals on the bottom. Make sure lid is ajar to allow moisture to escape.

title: quick trick clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan, mix potato slices, sauce mix, amount of water and milk called for on package, clam liquor, green onions and green pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in clams, 2 1/2 cups of milk and the butter; heat through.

title: steak roll-ups
directions: You will also need round toothpicks.
Cut off fat and bones of round steak and cut into triangles.
Flour each piece of steak and place a piece of bacon cut to the size of strip of meat.
Place a small amount of diced onion on bacon strip.
Roll up steak pieces and put toothpicks into pieces to hold together.
In a skillet put a small amount of oil.
Fry the steak pieces until brown.
Pour water over.
Roll up and cover until done, about an hour.
Makes it's own gravy.
Serve with mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: french bouillabaisse
directions: In a large kettle, melt butter.
Add onion and garlic and saute until golden.
Add wine, tomatoes, chicken broth, saffron and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and add 2-inch pieces of fish.
Add frozen rock lobster, cut into 1-inch crosswise slices (shell, too).
Simmer until fish becomes white (10 to 15 minutes). Add clams to soup.
Add peas; cover and simmer until shells open. Season to taste with salt and dash or two of cayenne.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve in bowls with French bread and a Caesar salad.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Add onion and celery.
Add a small amount of water and boil for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and kidney beans.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and pit avocados. Mash avocados and add lemon juice.
Mix in mayonnaise, onion, garlic salt and chili powder.
Stir until smooth, then add chopped tomato. (Do not add tomatoes until ready to serve.) Serve with chips.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Let cabbage and salt stand for 1 hour and drain.
Mix cabbage, peppers and carrots together.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix oleo and flour, add milk and cheese.
Drop by tablespoons 2 inches apart.
Bake at 425 degrees for 12 minutes or until done.

title: cook out stew
directions: Add enough water to cover carrots, potato and onion.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add peas and wieners and cook for 5 minutes more.
Drain.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Heat and serve.

title: crescent casserole
directions: Put 1 can of rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat and pour over crescent rolls.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Add hot pepper over cheese if desired.
Top with the second can of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: herbal baked chicken
directions: Wash and pat chicken dry; ladle melted butter over chicken. Then sprinkle on Season-All, garlic powder, rosemary, thyme and paprika.
Place in convection oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemony teff seed muffins
directions: Combine flour, teff, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. In a separate dish combine egg, milk, honey, oil and lemon juice. Combine dry and liquid ingredients.
Add lemon rind and vanilla. Stir vigorously until smooth.
Pour into lightly oiled muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Add lemon juice and pineapple (juice and all).
Add remaining ingredients.
Gel in refrigerator.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Add half of cream to this mixture.
Add soda and vinegar to remaining sour cream and stir to dissolve soda.
Add to sugar mixture and mix well.

title: praline sweet potatoes
directions: Boil peeled sweet potatoes 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain.
Cut in half or 1-inch slices and arrange in greased baking dish.
Bring cream to boil.
Stir in brown sugar until dissolved.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (238°).
Remove and beat in melted butter.
Add cinnamon and chopped pecans.
Drizzle over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll out to about 1/6 inch thick.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch rectangles.

title: vegetable sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and heat gently.
Do not allow to boil.
When serving, spoon over vegetables placed in a casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and place under a broiler until crumbs are brown, about 12 minutes.

title: fish fillets in foil #1
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in small saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice and dill weed.
In two 18 x 12-inch pieces of heavy duty foil, arrange fillets.
Divide butter mixture over fillets. Top fillets with 2 slices of onion.
Arrange potato and carrot strips on sides of fillets. Top fish with beans.
Fold foil over ingredients and seal.
Put sealed packages on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Blend salt and lemon juice with shortening.
Cream in sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add pineapple and sifted flour and soda.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: apple crunch
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Pare, core and slice apples. Combine sugar and cinnamon; mix with apples.
Put apples in greased 9 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Add flour and brown sugar to margarine and spread on top of the apple mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: egg nog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until light.
Beat in sugar; slowly stir in milk.
Then stir in whipped cream.
Just before serving, stir in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serves 20.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a well-greased loaf pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: tomato cheese dip
directions: Heat soup and water. Whisk gelatin into soup.
Blend mayonnaise and cream cheese. Add to soup.
Add all other ingredients and stir well. Pour into oiled mold or Saran wrapped bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and serve with wheat crackers.

title: yummy mound bars
directions: Microwave on
High the butter or oleo in an 8 x 12-inch glass baking
dish
until
melted.
Stir	in
crumbs and sugar until combined.
Press
mix
firmly
and	evenly	in bottom of dish. Stir
together
coconut and milk.
Spoon over crust and spread evenly.
Microwave	on
Medium (50 % power) uncovered 9 to 11 minutes, rotating dish once.
Microwave chips in uncovered glass dish
to
minutes
until melted.
Stir until smooth.	Spoon over coconut mix and spread to cover.
Refrigerate to set for 1 hour.
Cut into bars.

title: countryside potatoesmicrowave recipe
directions: Microwave the potatoes in the package 10-12 minutes or until steaming hot, turning package over once. Empty the potatoes into a greased 1 1/2 qt. Glass casserole dish. Add half and half, salt and chives. Mix with a fork, place the butter on the top and microwave uncovered for 5-6 minutes or until bubbling. Stir mixture and sprinkle the top with the cheese and paprika. Microwave at 50% power, uncovered 8-9 minutes or until tender. Serves 8.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Put in large pan.
Add Veg-All and tomatoes with juices and chopped onion.
Mix together.
Add rice. Cook on medium heat until rice is thick (about 1/2 hour).
Stir as needed to prevent from sticking.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.
Great for cold, rainy days!

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1 tablespoon milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Stir in 1 package Sweet 'N Low.
Fold in 1/2 of yogurt.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberries into cream cheese layer, saving several for garnish.

title: cheeseburger cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

title: fluffy orange cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar with electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or 12 cup fluted tube pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell and bake 40 to 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter.
Add powdered sugar and stir until well combined. Add your choice of food coloring and flavoring.
If desired, divide into two batches to make different colors and/or flavors.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on a sheet of waxed paper.
Press with fork.
Let stand, uncovered, about 4 hours or overnight until mints are firm and outside is dry, but inside is still moist and creamy.

title: rice and vegetable casserole
directions: Toast brown rice in skillet with 1 tablespoon olive oil until golden.
Add water and cook according to package directions.
Cook wild rice in separate pan.
Cook carrots, peas, broccoli and mushrooms until crisp.
Combine cooked rice and cooked vegetables. Add gravy mix, prepared according to package directions.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Heat through in 350° oven.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits, pecans and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir remaining sugar and the flavorings into whipped cream.
Fold in the fruit mixture.
Chill about 2 hours.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: grandma inez's kraut salad
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar for 2 minutes. Cool and pour over mixture of vegetables. Keeps very well.

title: roasted potatoes with garlic and herbs*
directions: In a large baking pan, toss potatoes with garlic, oil and herbs.
Salt and pepper to taste and roast in the middle of a preheated hot oven, 500°, stirring once, for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cornbread skillet meal
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion and ground beef; brown.
Add seasonings, soup and water; bring to a boil.
Beat egg slightly; add milk and mix with corn muffin mix, blending to moisten.
Pour evenly over meat mixture in skillet.
Cover and cook on low heat for about 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach into bite size pieces. Add next 4 ingredients.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O and pineapple. Add Cool Whip. Chill until sets. Also can add 1 carton cottage cheese. If want more, double the recipe.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello; add water and sugar.
Add pineapple.
Chop cranberries and orange; add to mixture and mix well.
Add pecans and chill.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add and mix well. Stir in raisins, nuts and water.

title: shrimp and vegetable risotto(for the microwave)
directions: Heat butter and oil in 14 x 11 x 2-inch dish, uncovered, at 100% power for 3 minutes.
Add scallion white, celery, parsley and rice and stir to coat.
Stir in broth and cook, uncovered, at 100% for 12 minutes.
Add asparagus, shrimp and peas and stir well. Cook, uncovered, for 12 minutes more.
Remove from oven.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Cover loosely with paper toweling and let stand for 8 to 10 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with scallion greens and cheese and serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish heavily.
Layer spuds and onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix Cheez Whiz, sour cream and soup. Pour over spuds and onions.
Cover with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "snacks"
directions: Melt butter. Add Worcestershire sauce. Cool slightly.
Pour over remaining ingredients in a large pan.
Mix with slotted spoon.
Cook at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir carefully every 10 to 15 minutes with slotted spoon. Cool thoroughly.
Keep in airtight containers.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In a saucepan, blend sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cornstarch and salt. Stir in 10 cups water. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Add lemon juice and coloring. Pour over apples
that have been packed in jars, leaving 1-inch cook space. Seal and boil in hot water bath for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients in pan with fork, beat vigorously 1 minute.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean (55 to 65 minutes).

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: gingersnap pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixing bowl, beat together eggs, pumpkin, brown sugar, orange peel, salt and spices at medium speed until blended.
Gradually beat in milk, evaporated milk and orange liqueur at low speed.
Pour into baked gingersnap crust. Fold narrow strips of foil around edge to prevent burning.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until center is still a bit soft but the rest of pie is set. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Brush chicken with salad dressing, coat with combined remaining ingredients. Place in 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: sinful pie
directions: Layer ingredients in pie shell.
Pour the Eagle Brand milk in middle of other ingredients.
Bake at 300° until brown and bubbly.

title: two's company chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts, skin side up, into a small shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with mushrooms and green pepper.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover dish with foil; bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil; top chicken with cheese. Return to oven uncovered and bake 10 more minutes.

title: macaroni cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all other ingredients together, reserving 1/4 cup of the cheese for garnish.
Bake in a large casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Just before it's done, garnish with the remaining 1/4 cup of cheese and cook for an additional 5 minutes.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Then add milk and water and mix well.
Knead dough until not sticky.
Roll dough into balls and then roll out until flat and shiny.
Fry in smoking grease until brown on both sides.
This Fry Bread is also good with cinnamon and sugar sprinkled on top.

title: crock-pot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onions.
Salt and pepper. Put in crock-pot.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Cook until meat is done. Very good if cooked for hour or so.

title: chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: In pie plate dip chicken into egg; coat with bread crumbs. In skillet over medium-low heat in hot oil, cook chicken 15 minutes or until browned on both sides and no longer pink.
Remove and keep warm.

title: turkey newburg casserole
directions: Lightly grease 1 quart baking dish.
Spread rice in even layers over bottom of dish.
Top with turkey.
Blend soup and milk in sauce pan, stirring constantly.
Heat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Pour sauce over turkey and rice in dish and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Cook 2 cups sugar in water until the syrup spins a thread when dropped from a spoon.
Add 2 cups berries and let boil 10 minutes, gently turning the berries occasionally.
Add 2 more cups sugar and 2 more cups berries and let cook in same manner.
Remove from heat.
Pour in shallow pan (glass) to let stand overnight.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: hilda's chicken and dumplings
directions: To make dumpling gravy, cook chicken, bone and dice it.
Save broth and add water to make 2 quarts.
In a large kettle, place broth.
Add coloring and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Make a thickening by mixing well melted oleo to flour.
Add to boiling broth.
Slowly add diced chicken and stir.
Ready for dumplings.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion, drain, saute mushrooms till tender. Combine with cheese and rice and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into lightly oiled casserole dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl to blend.
Place ingredients in electric or hand-crank ice cream maker. Be sure to use "ice cream salt" with ice to freeze this recipe!
If peach or strawberry flavor is desired, add with ingredients while mixing, but you will need to use 1 to 2 cups less milk with this mixture.

title: double-crust pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice. Combine the juice, sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan and cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from the heat and add pineapple, butter, lemon juice and the zest. Stir until butter melts. Pour into a pastry-lined pie plate. Cover with top crust; slit in several places to allow steam to escape. Seal and flute edges. Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Put potatoes, butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk in baking pan mixed together.

title: marcia's dessert cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes. Cool.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Eight slices white bread may be used, edges removed.

title: yum yum casserole
directions: Brown celery and onions with butter.
Add hamburg, salt and pepper; cook 1/2 hour or until brown.
Add soup, mushrooms and milk.
Mix. Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Cook onions until tender.
Add rest of ingredients to onion mixture.
Pour into 11 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Cut the orange sections in small pieces.
Add the cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle jello over the top and mix well. Add marshmallows (optional) and chill overnight.
This makes one 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan full.

title: blender mayonnaise
directions: In blender jar, blend egg, mustard and salt.
Then add vinegar or lemon juice.
Add oil very slowly.

title: foil baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread out 2 large squares of foil; lay 2 fish fillets on each square.
Dot each fillet with 1 teaspoon of butter, salt and pepper to taste and 1/2 teaspoon of paprika. Place half of the tomato, onion, green pepper and cucumber on top of fish on each foil square.
Sprinkle on the lemon juice and parsley flakes.
Seal all edges so fish is in 2 packets.
Bake, uncovered, in shallow dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: ship shrimp
directions: Peel Shrimp. Make a lengthwise slit down back of each shrimp to expose and wash sand vein. Heat water to a boil, then add shrimp and salt. Cover and heat to boil again.
Reduce heat to simmer. Simmer 5 minutes. Drain.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in a medium skillet over medium-high heat. Drain.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes and chili seasoning mix. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken dinner in the pot
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place chicken breasts in a large, heavy ovenware pot.
(An enamel coated cast-iron pot is best.)
Peel potatoes, slice 1/2-inch thick and place on top of chicken.

title: papaya-tomato sauce
directions: Peel, seed and dice papaya and jalapeno pepper.
Seed and chop tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Mix brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Put in large pan and stir every 10 minutes while baking at 200° for 1 hour.

title: sweet churn pickles
directions: Soak in brine water 14 days.
Remove, slice and soak in alum water overnight. Rinse, cover with vinegar and let set 6 hours. Drain vinegar and discard.

title: shrimp or tuna salad
directions: Cook noodles according to directions, drain.
Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Season with onion and and/or pepper to taste.
Add noodles to this.
Add Miracle Whip and mustard to this.
Slice boiled eggs on top and season with paprika.
Chill before serving.

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil water, sugar and cranberries until berries pop!

title: crawfish etouffee(a-z-fay)
directions: Season crawfish tails with salt and pepper; set aside.
In 1/4 cup oil, cook celery, onion, bell pepper and garlic until onions are wilted, stirring constantly.
Add 1 1/2 cups water, crawfish and tomatoes.
Bring to boil and cook over slow heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Dissolve cornstarch into 1/2 cup of water and add to mixture, if roux is used at this time.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice. Serves 4.

title: caleb's mashed potatoes
directions: Have your mommie boil and mash the potatoes.
Beat in the milk in small amounts.
Add margarine, salt and pepper; beat vigorously until potatoes are light and fluffy.
Delicious for breakfast, lunch and dinner, at least, I think so.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: german chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all cookie ingredients except nuts and sugar; blend well.
Stir in nuts, let stand 5 minutes.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into sugar; gently toss until sugar-coated and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.

title: dear abby's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Add to eggs and add pecans.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: granny's chew bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add melted margarine and vanilla.
Beat eggs and add to flour mixture.
Then add pecans and coconut.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Drop a tablespoon of mixture for each hush puppy into hot deep fat (360°) or into fat in which fish has been fried.
Fry a few at a time until golden brown. Serve hot.

title: sugar chocolate cookies(a must at christmastime, easy and good.)
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar. Beat 1 minute. Fold in flour. Lightly grease cookie sheet; drop dough by teaspoon. Flatten, then sprinkle with candie shots. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown ground turkey, add rest of ingredients and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring often.
Add water if chili is too thick.

title: pineapple coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss lightly with salad dressing.

title: simple banana pudding
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk together, cool, add whipped cream. Put layer of vanilla wafers crumbs in dish. Spread small amount of cream mixture on crumbs. Add sliced bananas on top. Spread rest of cream mixture. Sprinkle a few wafers on top.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spoon undrained sauerkraut into a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe baking dish.
Layer with corned beef and cheese.
Mix mayonnaise and salad dressing in small bowl until blended.
Spread over cheese.
Top with tomato slices.
Toss bread crumbs with butter in bowl.
Sprinkle over tomatoes.
Microwave on Medium for 12 to 14 minutes; let stand a few minutes before serving.
(May bake at 350° for 40 minutes instead of cooking in microwave.)

title: yam, berry mallow crisp
directions: Combine flour, sugar, oats and cinnamon, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Arrange yams and cranberries in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish; sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and broil until lightly brown.

title: ritz cracker cookies
directions: Melt milk and dates in double boiler until thick, then add pecans.
Spread this mixture on Ritz crackers and bake for 3 minutes at 350°.
When cool, frost with icing.

title: slush punch(serves 50)
directions: Boil sugar and water together.
Add lemon jello, stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
When cool, add pineapple juice and juice of 5 lemons.
Pour in 3 half-gallon milk cartons and freeze.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add enough mayonnaise to make it smooth.
Add cayenne pepper to taste.
Remember cayenne gets hotter the longer it sits.
Better if it sits overnight.

title: broccoli-ham ring
directions: Stir and taste and add more Durkee if you like.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight or more.
(Will last about 3 to 4 weeks refrigerated).
Peel and slice thin the tomatoes (no more than 1/8-inch).
Place on dry paper towels overnight.
This prevents soggy sandwiches.
Trim bread edges off of 4 loaves of bread (2 white/2 wheat) or use small cocktail sandwich bread.
Spread thinly with sauce.

title: oven meatballs
directions: Combine beef, rice, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and onion. Shape into meatballs and place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup and water together and pour over meatballs.
Cover tightly. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: oven glazed chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange chicken.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood supreme
directions: Saute green pepper in butter until tender; add 2 tablespoons flour.
In a double boiler place soup, cheese and soda.
Melt.
Add sauteed pepper, milk, cream and fish.
Heat well and serve with rice or crackers.

title: egg casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Layer ham, cheese and onions over bread cubes.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk, mustard and paprika.
Pour mixture over layered ingredients. Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: speedy chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place egg yolks, sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in heavy saucepan.
Gradually add milk; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, to full boil.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Stir and pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Mix dressing and pepper in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly. Refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix together first three ingredients into crumbs; save about 1 cup of crumbs for top.
Add other ingredients to crumb mixture. Sprinkle saved cup of crumbs on top of cakes.
Bake about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: corn or egg bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add buttermilk and egg, stirring until combined.
Melt drippings in skillet or pan and add to the batter.
Pour into a very hot pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill dough.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut with favorite cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Decorate with colored sugar or sprinkles or frost and decorate.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in salted water.
Set aside to cool.
Mix in a casserole dish, sugar, flour and oil.
Beat eggs and mix with other ingredients.
Add cooked rice and milk.
Mix well.
Add flavoring and raisins.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender.
Drain and cool.
Place carrots in large bowl.
Add pepper and onion.
Mix seasonings with soup.
Then gradually stir in vinegar and oil, blending well. Pour soup mixture over vegetables.
Seal container and turn several times to mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate 24 hours, allowing flavors to blend.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: summer fruit cake(by peggy mann)
directions: Grease pan.
Pour cherry pie filling on bottom.
Spread pineapple on top of cherry filling.
Next, layer the coconut. Then sprinkle a box of white cake mix over the fruit.
Sprinkle a few nuts over the cake mix.

title: quick butter bean soup
directions: Quick and easy tasty soup.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer pork chops, sliced potatoes and onions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season to taste.
Cover with mushroom soup for a sauce. Cover with foil.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes an easy and quick meal.

title: slow cooker minestrone
directions: Combine ground beef and beans in a slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high for 2 hours.
Add all remaining ingredients except macaroni and stir to combine.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
One hour before cooking is done, stir macaroni into contents of slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.

title: little league barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour or so.

title: bacon and broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Cook sugar, water, vinegar, flour, salt and pepper until sauce is clear and thick.
Cool, then add mayonnaise, mustard and bacon.

title: angel food cake pie
directions: Tear up angel food cake.
Put on bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan. Cover with vanilla pudding.
Cover pudding with cherry pie filling and top with Dream Whip.
Garnish with coconut flakes, chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: easy lasagna and caesar salad
directions: Separate lettuce, discarding tough outer leaves.
Wash and dry thoroughly.
Tear into bite size pieces.
In small bowl, mash anchovies.
Stir in lemon juice, mustard, salt and pepper.
Whisk in oil until well blended.
Place lettuce in salad bowl; pour dressing over.
Toss gently.
Add remaining ingredients; toss briefly.
Prepare lasagna according to package directions.
Remove to serving plates and serve with salad.
Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in butter until transparent; add meat and brown. Add seasonings and sour cream.
Cook until tender and add flour if it needs to be thickened.
Serve with noodles and salad or veggie.

title: spicy zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in one bowl; stir.
Grease two loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for one hour.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Press graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350°.
Cool and top with cherry pie filling (1 can) and 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip.

title: jellied 3 fruit sauce
