directions: Cut apples and orange in chunks and put through food chopper with the cranberries, using coarse blade.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
Cut up lettuce, onion and tomato.
Crush Doritos.
Mix all the preceding with 1/2 package dry taco mix.
Pour dressing over.
Add other 1/2 package of dry mix.
Make sure hamburger is cool before adding cheese.
Stir well and serve.

title: veg-all chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except margarine and crumbs. Put in baking dish.
Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs. Spread crumb mixture on chicken mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or more.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown together:
beef, green pepper, celery, onion, garlic, basil and anise seed.
When done, drain well of any fat.
Add rice, spaghetti sauce and water to the brown meat mixture.
Simmer this 5 to 10 minutes on low heat.
Chop 1/2 head of cabbage; layer on bottom of casserole dish.
Layer Mozzarella cheese on top of cabbage layer.
Pour meat mixture on top of cheese layer.
Cover dish tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until cabbage is done.
(This is same taste as cabbage rolls.)

title: salad dressing
directions: Put everything in pan and bring to a full boil stirring constantly.
Take off stove, add a little mustard and butter the size of a walnut, stir good and let cool.
Cover with wax paper. You can put a little mayonnaise in salad dressing when you use it. Stores well in refrigerator.

title: macaroni salad (1)
directions: Add green pepper, onions and tomatoes to macaroni.
Then add Italian dressing.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first three ingredients thoroughly.
Add milk and corn, mix again.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake 350° for one hour or until firm.

title: coconut cream flan
directions: Spread coconut in a thin layer in a large baking pan.
Spread almonds in small baking pan.
Bake both in a 350° oven 5 to 10 minutes or until golden, stirring once or twice; set aside.

title: chili beef stuffing bake
directions: Mix contents of stuffing mix pouch, 1 1/2 cups hot water and 1/4 c. margarine, cut up, in large bowl just until moistened. Set aside. Mix remaining ingredients in 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Top with stuffing. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh tomato pie
directions: Mix water and Bisquick and spread in 9-inch pie plate.
Slice tomatoes over Bisquick.
Mix shredded cheese, onions and mayonnaise and spread over tomatoes.
Add a dash of salt, pepper and oregano and bake in 350° oven
for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, sugar, egg whites and vanilla until smooth.
Add flour, soda and oatmeal; mix well.
Form into small balls and bake on a greased cookie sheet at 375° until done.

title: pie pastry
directions: Mix and divide into 3 equal portions. May be frozen for future use.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Longer, the better.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with pita or bagel chips.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix next 4 ingredients and add yeast mixture; mix well.
Cover and let raise until double (about 1 hour, can refrigerate at this point for later use).
Spread in greased jelly roll pan.
Pour tomato sauce over dough and sprinkle with Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.
Add other ingredients as desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add egg.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir into butter mixture.
Stir floured berries into mixture with enough milk to make a fairly thick batter.
Bake in muffin cups for 15 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven until golden brown.

title: chicken and rice with mushrooms
directions: Brown chicken and cut into cubes. Mix chicken, rice, nuts and mushrooms and 1 cup of cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix soup, Worcestershire and garlic to taste.
Mix soup into other ingredients.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot through.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add pineapple (undrained).
Mix cream cheese with milk and beat until smooth, then add to jell-O and pineapple mixture.
Add grated carrots and vinegar.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: 14 carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon together; add sugar and oil, mixing well.
Beat in eggs.
Add carrots, drained pineapple and nuts.
Spoon batter into 3 (10-inch) round layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Spread frosting between layers and on top of cake.

title: grandma schreck's frosting
directions: Bring to boil cream and sugar to soft ball stage (248°). Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until spreading consistency (I use electric mixer, but she used a wooden spoon). Spread on chocolate cake.
Work fast, because it sets up very quickly.
I double this recipe for a 9 x 13 cake because my family loves it.
I think I am the only one that has luck making it, and my grandchildren always request this cake.

title: simple salad elegante
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients, except salad greens. Cover and marinate in refrigerator, stirring occasionally, 4 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Break cake into pieces and cover bottom of large bowl. Cut up strawberries and add sugar. Place some strawberries on top of cake and add layers of pudding. Continue to layer cake, strawberries and pudding. Top with Cool Whip and let cool in the refrigerator 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together Wesson oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix cocoa, food coloring and vanilla; add vinegar together.
Combine these; add flour that has been sifted with salt and soda alternately with buttermilk to mixture.
Bake at 350° in 3 cake pans that have been greased and dusted with flour.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove and cool on cake racks and ice.

title: tomato salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients but add oil last and mix in blender well.
Store in refrigerator.
Improves with age.

title: canadian pea soup
directions: Wash and soak the peas.
Put them in a large saucepan with all the ingredients.
Bring to a boil and let boil 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until peas are cooked.

Season with salt and pepper (a few kernels of hominy corn may be added towards the end of the cooking time.) Serve as is or pureed by passing the soup through a sieve or a mincer or blend in an electric grinder beater.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove bones and skin.
Cut up chicken and place in baking dish; mix chicken broth and chicken soup.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix all other ingredients. Pour over top of chicken and bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Buy chicken at store, take out of bag and put in a jug.
Put jug in oven and cook 3 days and make sure you put 1 onion in the jug and that makes it taste good!

title: baked chicken with rice and corn dressing
directions: Brush chicken with butter and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper. Bake in shallow casserole, skin side up, at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: southern fried catfish
directions: Preheat oil to 350°. Sprinkle both sides of catfish with seasoning. In a separate bowl, combine the flour and the cornmeal. Dredge the fillets in the flour mixture and place in the hot oil. Deep-fry for 7 to 8 minutes, until done. Drain onto paper towels.

title: master mix corn bread
directions: Stir cornmeal, salt and sugar into mix.
Combine milk and beaten egg; add to mix, stirring until blended.
Bake in greased pan in hot oven (400°) for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 x 6-inch pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, form ball and refrigerate over night. You can double this recipe to serve a larger group of people. Serve with Townhouse or Ritz crackers.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil 30 minutes.
Seal in jars. Yields 6 pints.

title: hot wassail
directions: Mix in coffee pot pineapple juice, apple cider and orange juice. Squeeze lemon juice into pot. Put spices in the top of the pot. Perk 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: wassail
directions: Cook in crock-pot, covered, on high for 1 hour then turn to low 4 to 8 hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and cook in double boiler until thick.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites, spread on top and brown.

title: herb-parmesan bread
directions: Brush frozen loaf with 1 tablespoon butter.
Cover; thaw at room temperature 2 to 3 hours or in refrigerator 6 to 10 hours. Sprinkle loaf with 1/3 cup cheese; knead until well blended.
Cut dough into thirds.
On lightly floured surface, roll each third in a 25-inch rope.
Braid ropes together.

title: pizza bread
directions: Mix last 6
ingredients
together
well and spread over split bread.
Place
on
large
sheet
of heavy foil, bringing foil over edge of bread so it will not cook too fast.
Bake 30 minutes at 250°.

title: risotto orientale(turkish)
directions: Using
a
large
cast-iron or heavy pan with tight lid, put oil
into
pan.
Get it sizzling hot, then put in the dry, uncooked
rice
and
keep
it
moving.
Toast rice to a golden color.
Remove
immediately
from
heat
and pour in 2 cups of water, adding turmeric.
Cover tightly.
Cook on slow heat for 15 minutes.
Add the vegetables and cook for another 10 to 15 minutes, depending on the vegetables.
Be sure to use low heat when cooking rice and vegetables.

title: paula's chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken, cool, debone and cut into small pieces. Mix both cans of enchilada sauce and set aside. Put chicken and mix with 1/2 cup of the mixed sauces. Put 3/4 cup cheese in with chicken and sauce. Add 1/2 of the onion. Mix sour cream into meat mixture (optional, but very good). Place 2 skillets on stove. On low heat, pour cooking oil (enough to cover bottom) into one skillet and the remaining mixed sauce in the other. Fry one tortilla at a time in the oil until just soft, not crisp. Then dip in the sauce mixture. Put in baking pan. Add chicken mixture, roll up and proceed to next tortilla. When finished, pour the remaining sauce over all and top with remaining cheese and onion. Bake at 350° until bubbly. Let sit about 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix zucchini, eggs, sugar and oil together with mixer.
Add dry ingredients to zucchini mixture and beat with mixer.
Add chopped pecans; mix well and pour into a well sprayed Bundt pan or angel food pan.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until pick comes out clean, at 300°.
Let cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool completely and frost with any icing or serve plain.
You also can dust with powdered sugar.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice per box instructions.
With remaining margarine, saute onion and mushrooms.
Mix chicken, soup, onion and mushrooms together; add to rice mixture.
Stir in almonds, reserving several for later.
Pour into casserole dish; top with remaining almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: very berry clafouti
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, beat eggs with an electric mixer on medium speed until frothy.
Add milk, flour, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in the shredded peel.
Put into a greased
9-inch quiche dish or pie plate.
Sprinkle with dried fruit.

title: rolled lasagne with pesto
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain and set aside.
When cool enough to handle, carefully separate noodles.
In medium size bowl, beat egg, then blend in Ricotta and Jack cheese, oregano, parsley and garlic.
Spread Ricotta mixture evenly over each noodle.
Roll from end to end.
Stand rolled noodles on end in a greased shallow 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Blend cream and Pesto; pour evenly over lasagne rolls.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: magic muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% bran cereal and set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and All-Bran.
Add dry ingredients to the margarine mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Add 100% whole bran mixture last.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in flour and salt.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to batter, mixing well. Spoon into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Stir baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Turn onto surface dusted with baking mix; roll in baking mix to coat. Shape into ball; knead 10 times.
Press dough evenly on bottom and up side of pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cook ground beef, onion, chili powder, garlic and oregano in 10-inch skillet, stirring occasionally, until beef is brown; drain.
Stir 3/4 cup of cheese, tomatoes and chilies into beef mixture.
Spoon onto crust, sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese is hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken bog
directions: Fry bacon in big pot.
When done, leave grease in pot and add water until pot is 1/2 full.
Bring to a boil.
Cut up onion; place into boiling water.
Add 7 teaspoons pepper and 3 teaspoons salt.
Add chicken and boil until done.
Cut sausage and place into boiling water.
Wait 20 minutes and add rice, 2 teaspoons pepper and meat tenderizer.
Cook until rice is done and enjoy a southern meal.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour, and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract; mix well.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: To cake mix, add 1 tablespoon coconut flavoring.
Mix and bake according to directions on box.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Boil together milk, sugar and 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring.
Pour over hot cake.
Put coconut on cake.
Let cool.
Spread one large container of Cool Whip.
Add remaining coconut.

title: pizzas on rye (party snacks)
directions: Mix well and spoon and spread on small rye bread.
Bake in 350° oven (preheated) for 20 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs; add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: breaded dandelion blossoms
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Gently wash the flowers and drain.
Do not pat them dry.
Carefully coat them with the batter.
Deep fry to a light golden brown.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine ingredients and store in tightly covered jar.

title: chicken cashew salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together. Spoon individual portions into lettuce cups. Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add ham, green onions and Worcestershire sauce and beat until blended. Place on serving plate and shape into ball. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease
and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and cinnamon and blend. Stir in carrots and undrained pineapple.
Bake about 1 hour.
Cool completely and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once and stir until dough follows the fork around bowl.
Place dough on lightly floured surface, gently patting out dough to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; cook until thick, then cool.
When cool, stir in mandarin oranges and then Cool Whip.
Let set.

title: grandma's cheesecake
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and eggs, until light and fluffy. Beat in sugar gradually.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
In a separate cup, mix flour and cornstarch together.
Gradually add to the cream cheese mixture.
Add the butter and sour cream.
Pour into a greased 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° until set in center (about 1 hour).
Turn oven off and leave in oven for 2 hours.
Chill several hours and serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and serve over ice.

title: hot bacon and swiss dip
directions: Microwave cream cheese for 30 seconds.
Mix with mayonnaise, Swiss cheese and onion.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate.
Cook bacon until crisp; crumble along with the crackers and sprinkle on top. Microwave on High for 4 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Use pita or bagel chips to dip.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Heat milk, then cool a little; add oleo, sugar and salt.
Add eggs and flour.
Stir and knead.
Raise until double.
Knead down again.
Divide into 4.
Roll out onto a 16-inch circle.
Cut into 12 to 16 pie shaped pieces.
Roll from the wide end to the point. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry chews
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cherries and nuts into a bowl.
Add eggs and stir thoroughly.
Spread into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan (it will seem not enough, but spread real thin).
Bake in oven at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar if desired.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat shortening and butter together with mixer on medium for 30 seconds. Add sugar, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, cocoa powder and powdered sugar. Beat well and add the rest of the ingredients except flour, chips and nuts. Add flour slowly, after beating the other ingredients well. Lastly, add the chips and nuts as desired. Drop dough on cookie sheets by rounded spoonfuls. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Transfer to wire rack and cool. Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: english toffee trifle
directions: Sprinkle cake with Kahlua and let set 5 minutes.
Mix pudding and cake together; set aside. Pour whipping cream and coffee into mixing bowl.
Let stand 1 minute.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken; add sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating until mixture forms soft peaks.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400°.

title: stuffed hamburger birds
directions: Mix hamburger and milk. Make 5 to 6 flat patties.
Mix stuffing with water until damp.
Place stuffing on patties.
Roll patty around stuffing.
In same bowl mix rest of ingredients. Pour over hamburger birds.	Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine
in
x
8-inch pan.
Mix together the sugar, flour
and
baking
powder.
Then
add
the milk.
Pour mixture over the melted margarine and stir once.
Then pour in the fruit. Do not mix this again.
It will mix itself when it is cooking. Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: party mints
directions: Mix the cream cheese and extract until cream cheese is softened.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Place dough into small molds or roll out and cut with miniature cutters.

title: broccoli casserole(green rice)
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine for 5 to 10 minutes, until tender.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Best if baked, but can also be microwaved on High for about 20 minutes, stirring and turning at 10 minutes and again at 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer cauliflower, lettuce, onion, bacon, cheese and sugar. Just before serving, add Miracle Whip and toss.

title: philadelphia cream cheese dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese and crushed pineapple together.
Dice cherries and stir in.
Chill for two hours.
Makes pretty dip for the holidays.

title: russian cream(serves 6)
directions: Combine sugar, water and gelatin in small saucepan and blend well.
Let stand 4 to 5 minutes.
Place over medium heat and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually blend in cream.
Combine sour cream and vanilla in medium bowl. Gradually add hot sugar mixture, whisking constantly until smooth. Pour into 6 wine glasses or dessert dishes.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Garnish with sliced strawberries or blueberries.

title: jogging in a jar
directions: Mix well together.
Drink 2 ounces each day before meals.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, spice, sugar and oil together, then add one egg at a time.
Then add carrots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in two 8-inch round pans.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: First, put in your butter or shortening, then put in salt, baking soda and eggs.
Then mix in the brown sugar.
Gradually add sugar, then put your vanilla in.
Then mix all the dry ingredients first, then put your cups of flour in and then the Nestle chips. Then mix in all the ingredients together until it becomes a smooth texture.
Bake it at 350°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine graham crackers with margarine and sugar. Mix well, then press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 4 minutes. Set aside to cool.

title: caramel nut pie(very easy)
directions: Combine the milk and brown sugar in a double boiler; cook until thick.
Pour in prepared pie crust.
Top with whipped topping and nuts if desired.

title: banana nut pound cake
directions: Mix salad oil, sugar, eggs, flour, soda and salt well together.
Then mix buttermilk, bananas and vanilla in the blender.
Add the mixtures together and add pecans and coconut. Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let it set in the pan for 15 minutes before turning out.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Put whole vanilla wafers in bottom of 15 muffin cups.
Combine next four ingredients.
Fill cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° until top cracks (20 to 23 minutes).
Chill.
Top with cherries.
Yields 15 tarts.

title: whacky cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a flour sifter and sift into an 8-inch square pan.
Then make 3 holes in the mixture.
In the first hole, put 1 tablespoon of vinegar; in second hole, put 1 teaspoon of vanilla and in the third hole, put 5 tablespoons melted butter.
Then pour 1 cup of cold water over all.
Mix well in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Icing cake in pan.
Nuts may be added.

title: strawberry chiffon-style pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in graham crackers and 2 packs Equal. Press mixture evenly in a 9-inch pie plate.
Press onto bottom and up sides to form a firm even crust.
Chill about 1 hour or until firm.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Mix in the rest of ingredients.
Grease casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or stuff turkey or chicken.
Add more chicken broth, if needed, while mixing.

title: vincie's salad
directions: Dissolve dry jello with fruit.
Add all the other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well with mixer.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° (preheated) for 50 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: In a large pan add canola oil.
Coat pan.
Cut up chicken into strips or large cubes.
Place in pan with oil.
Season with onion powder, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook chicken until well done. In a saucepan follow package directions and make Stove Top stuffing.
In small saucepan, cook broccoli until tender.
Layer chicken, then broccoli, then stuffing in casserole dish.
Add 1/4 can soup between layers and add rest to top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: carrot pickle
directions: Pare and cut carrots.
Cook until firm (not soft).
While carrots are cooking, in another saucepan add tomato soup, vinegar and sugar over medium heat unti thick.
Drain carrots while still hot.
Put in dish with onion and green pepper slices.
Pour sauce over carrots.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: catfish amandine
directions: In a
large
frying pan over medium heat, melt 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Saute fish, turning once until fish just flakes when tested with
a fork.
Transfer to platter and keep warm.
In the same
pan,	add
remaining margarine, lemon peel and lemon juice. Saute
1 minute, reducing heat, if necessary to
avoid burning. Pour
sauce
over
fillets.
Garnish
with parsley and lemon slices.

title: apple cabbage slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine Butter Buds, yogurt, vinegar and sugar. Add remaining ingredients and toss to mix well.
Chill.

title: dallas drumsticks
directions: Sprinkle drumsticks with salt and pepper.
Combine crumbs, cheese and chives.
Dip chicken in butter; then roll in crumb mixture to coat well.
Place in a flat baking pan lined with aluminum foil.
Drizzle remaining butter over chicken.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until browned and cooked.
Makes 6 servings.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool, then cut into bars.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir until creamy and pour into buttered pan.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo in Pyrex dish.
Add fruit.
Mix flour, sugar and milk in separate bowl.
Stir in fruit and bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: aunt bee's apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1/2 cup butter and cream cheese.
Let come to room temperature.
Add 2 cups flour, blend well.
Chill. Roll out half of dough and place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Reserve the remaining dough for the top crust.

title: chicken continental
directions: After browning chicken, combine remaining ingredients (except rice) in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Put rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour all but 1/2 cup sauce over rice.
Stir.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
Pour 1/2 cup remaining sauce on chicken pieces.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: eggs in bologna cups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 6 muffin cups with some shortening. Melt 2 teaspoons shortening in skillet over low heat.
Place 3 slices of bologna in the skillet and fry until the edges curl and center puffs.
Lift each slice into a muffin cup.
Repeat with remaining bologna.
Break 1 egg into the center of each bologna slice to hold it down.
Pour 1 teaspoon of milk over each egg. Sprinkle eggs lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake uncovered in a 375° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until eggs are set. Loosen with knife and serve.

title: pasta 'n beef in mustard cream sauce
directions: Cut breakfast beef into small pieces.
Cook until crisp. Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons fat.
Cook celery and green onions in fat until tender.
Add wine and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes. Pour in cream, stirring rapidly.
Continue to stir until mixture boils.
Simmer about 5 minutes, until thick.
Stir in mustard and parsley.
Top sauce with cooked fettucini, grapes and beef.

title: spam treats
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with toasted bread.

title: grasshoppers
directions: In blender, combine ice cream, creme de cacao and creme de menthe.
Cover and blend until smooth.

title: cheese potato puff
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in salt water until tender; drain and mash thoroughly.
Add butter, cheese, milk and salt.
Heat until butter and cheese are melted.
Fold in 2 eggs, beaten, to the cheese and potatoes.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples: cut in eighths.
Arrange in unbaked pie shell. Mix 1/2 cup sugar with the cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine.
Pat into an oblong baking dish.
Cover with bananas.
Blend the eggs, confectioners sugar and 2 sticks margarine for 15 minutes.
Pour over bananas. Spread pineapple over this.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans and decorate with cherries. Chill and serve in squares.

title: sauteed string beans
directions: Steam or partially cook string beans.
In skillet, saute minced garlic and bread crumbs in olive oil.
When garlic starts to sizzle, add string beans and mix until blended.

title: mit kartoffein(german fish pie)
directions: Sprinkle fish pieces with salt and refrigerate 1/2 hour. Rinse and dry.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat butter in skillet and add onions.
Saute over low heat until onions lightly brown.

title: chicken spread
directions: Mix well.
Serve with crackers or cocktail rye bread

title: gouda cheese ball
directions: Place rolls flat on a cookie sheet.
Press seams together to make large rectangle.
Lightly brush on Hellmann's dijonnaise mustard or any other spicy mustard.
Place Gouda cheese in center of dough.
Bring up sides of dough and twist together on top, sealing seams tightly.
Brush outside with beaten egg white.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: old fashioned creamed corn
directions: Cook corn according to directions on package.
Melt butter and cream cheese in pan.
Add sugar.
Mix into cooked corn.
Heat all together.
Serve.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip together.
Layer vanilla wafers and cut up bananas.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over this.
Put another layer of wafers and bananas.
Pour rest of mixture over this.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; reserve egg whites for meringue.
Add some milk to yolks and pour into sugar and flour mixture.
Pour in rest of milk and boil until thickened.
Add coconut and pour into pie shell.
Prepare meringue by beating egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar with mixer until very stiff.
Add meringue to top of pie. Bake at 325° until meringue is brown.

title: old fashioned butterscotch pie
directions: Blend well and set aside.

title: sourdough oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until light.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift flour with soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Add creamed mixture alternately with sourdough starter, beating well after each addition.
Fold in quick-cooking oatmeal, nuts and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden, about 10 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the pretzels, pecans, margarine and sugar.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix together the cream cheese, whipped topping and powdered sugar. Put on the first layer.
Dissolve the jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Stir until thick.
Put over second layer. Refrigerate.

title: weight watchers dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours. Chill overnight if possible.
Serve with raw vegetables or chips.

title: red beet pickles
directions: Wash, cook and skin beets. Be careful not to cut beets while washing or they will "bleed." Cut in desired size.
Bring all ingredients (except beets) to a boil. Add beets.
Seal in clean, warm jars.

title: key largo roast pork
directions: Place pork roast in non-metallic container.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over pork roast.
Cover container with 2 layers of plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove meat from marinade and set marinade aside.
Place meat on rack in roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes per pound.
After 1/2 of baking time, remove from oven and pour marinade over meat.
Return to oven and finish baking.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: debbie's cherry cheesecake
directions: Make cake according to box.
Add softened cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Line ladyfingers along bottom and sides of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Pour in filling.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Top with small can of cherries.
Serves 8.

title: swedish apple pie(the gatto way)
directions: Slice apples to fill a 9-inch pie dish nice and high.
Toss with apple pie spices.

title: venus de milo's orzo soup
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into a large saucepan and fill to 1/2 full with water.
Cook until ingredients (ground beef and onions) are done.
Add the vegetables; bring to a boil and add orzo.
Cook until orzo is done.

title: savory chicken pie
directions: In a saucepan brown sausage and drain on paper towels.
Pour off fat.
In same pan, melt butter and blend in flour and salt. Cook until thickened.
(I use more broth to make gravy thinner and more of it.)
Add sausage, chicken and peas.
Heat through.
Pour into baking dish and top with pastry.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, sugar, salt and spices.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake about 45 minutes at 375°.

title: molasses whoopie pies
directions: Mix eggs, Crisco, molasses, sugar and vinegar.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients, then combine.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: tuna pocket
directions: Process cottage cheese until smooth; add next 6 ingredients. Bake in 350° oven.
Can bake 15 minutes wrapped in foil or serve cold.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add cranberry sauce and pineapple (tall can) with juice.
Allow to thicken.
Add chopped pecans and pour into mold.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with greens and serve with Yogurt Dressing.

title: plantation chicken
directions: Boil chicken until meat falls off bone.
Cook celery in broth. Saute
onions
and pepper in butter until tender.	Add flour and milk; stir well until thickened.
Add soup, stirring constantly until thickened (like a white sauce).
Add chicken, celery	and pimento.
Salt to taste.
Serve over already baked Pepperidge Farm pastry shells.

title: easy potato soup
directions: In a medium saucepan melt margarine; add onion and cook, stirring constantly for 5 minutes or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.

title: crustless zucchini quiche
directions: Combine zucchini, green onions, chiles and tomato.
Add cheeses; mix well.
Pam spray pie plate.
Put above ingredients in pie plate.
Mix together egg substitute, milk, garlic powder and pepper.
Pour over cheese and vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set in center.
Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, blend all dry ingredients. Add oil, eggs and vanilla; mix well. (No electric mixer necessary; I use a large wire whisk.) Add apples last. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes and apricots
directions: Place potatoes in oblong baking dish.
Drain apricots, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Place apricots over potatoes.
Combine in saucepan the sugar, cinnamon, cornstarch, apricot juice and orange juice.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat and add butter and pecans.
Pour over potatoes and apricots.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook for 35 minutes or until done.

title: ham and broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Partially bake pie crust.
Mix milk, eggs and some cheese.
Pour just enough egg mixture into pie shell to cover bottom.
Alternately layer ham, broccoli and cheese.
Pour rest of egg mixture over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice eggplant approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Flour.
Brown. Mix hamburger and remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Take hamburg mixture and cover each eggplant individually.
Layer eggplant with either or both Mozzarella or Provolone cheese.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Season with Italian seasonings.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea salsa
directions: Place peas in colander.
Rinse with cold water; drain. Combine tomatoes and next seven ingredients in medium bowl; stir in peas.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: crab stuffed portabella mushrooms
directions: In a small sauce pan melt butter; add flour, one half of bay seasoning, and pepper, blend well.	Slowly add milk, stir and cook until thickened; then add cheese, stir until melted.
Set aside. Mix together crab, lemon juice, worcestershire sauce, mustard and green onions;

pour milk mixture over this and mix together. Stuff mushrooms with equal amounts of crab mixture, top with crumbs and parmesan cheese, as you desire.	Place mushrooms in baking dish, bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with a salad, french bread and wine.

title: peanut whirls cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Roll out cookie dough to rectangle 1/4-inch in thickness.
Melt chocolate bits over hot water and cool slightly.
Spread on rolled cookie dough.
Roll jelly roll fashion.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Slice with sharp knife into thin slices.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: heavenly healthy garden quiche
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and garlic in margarine.
In bowl, toss Lite-line pieces with flour.
Add onion mixture and remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly oiled or sprayed 9-inch pie plate. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until set.
Serves 6.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat with electric mixer at medium speed until creamy.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour and baking soda to creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool on baking sheet for 2 minutes.
Move to cooling rack.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Drain cherries.
Juice lemons.
Whip cream and fold in all ingredients.
Pour into 2 cooked pie shells.
Chill and serve.

title: honey-oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix
milk,
oil, egg and honey to remaining ingredients (that have
been mixed).	Mix just enough to moisten.
Fill 12 greased-floured or paper lined cupcake pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Add Cool Whip.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put a layer of graham crackers, half the pudding mixture, a second layer of graham crackers, the rest of the pudding and a third layer of crackers.
Spread the chocolate icing over the top and refrigerate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze water from spinach.
In medium bowl, mix spinach and all other ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate until ready to serve on crackers or chips.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix seasonings in bowl and add crackers, a few at a time. Drain for a couple hours on paper towels and store in airtight containers.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix and shake in jar.

title: sweet vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together, except avocado, into a dish with a cover.

Mix marinade ingredients into a dish with a cover and shake well. Pour marinade over vegetable mixture and refrigerate, covered, for several hours or overnight. Drain liquid before serving, if desired. Add chopped avocado just prior to serving or optional.

title: okra succotash
directions: Saute onion in large skillet with garlic and pepper.
Add other ingredients and simmer together for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage cheese strata
directions: Cooking Time: About 1 hour.

title: chart house mud pie
directions: Crush wafers. Add butter.
Mix well.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with ice cream.
Put into freezer until ice cream is firm.
Top with fudge sauce.
You may put sauce in freezer to make spreading easier.
You may store up to 10 hours in freezer.
Serve on chilled plates. Top with whipped cream and slivered toasted almonds.

title: holiday party mix
directions: Melt white chocolate; pour over nuts, pretzels, Chex cereal and M&M's.

title: chicken casserole bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and 1/2 cup milk.
In kettle, melt remaining 6 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add remaining 3 cups of milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in chicken gravy, chicken, pimento and noodles. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 25 minutes.
Combine bread crumbs and 1 1/2 tablespoons melted butter; blend in processed American cheese.
Sprinkle edges of casserole. Bake for 10 minutes more.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: christmas berry punch
directions: Mix ahead cranberry juice, pineapple juice and thawed strawberries.
Chill.
Just before serving, cut sherbet into 16 squares per pint.
Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Put salmon on broiler pan.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl and spread over steaks.
Bake in oven 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour; stir together good.
Add milk, broth and cream.
Stir until mixture thickens and becomes bubbly. Reduce heat.
Add chicken and pepper and heat for about 5 more minutes.

title: family favorite puffy brunch or dinner omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat egg whites with electric mixer on high speed, until stiff, but not dry.
In small mixing bowl, add water, salt and pepper to the egg yolks. Beat with beater used before until thick and lemon colored.
Gently fold this mixture into beaten egg whites, being careful not to overmix.

title: icebox dessert
directions: Filling:
Cook pineapple, butter, eggs, sugar and tapioca until thick like pudding.
Add nuts when cool.

title: lemon cake
directions: In a large bowl with electric mixer blend cake mix, dry gelatin, oil and water.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix in lemon juice.
Pour into greased and floured baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cake is removed from oven, pierce with a fork and frost at once with the glaze.

title: cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour and cream until it drops off spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in cooked mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in casserole.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: stewed fish
directions: Steam fish through in pan with water, salt and pepper.
Remove fish from pan.
Leave water.

title: baba ghannouj(appetizer)
directions: Trim stem from eggplant.
Bake at 400° until flesh is soft and skins begin to crisp.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Split eggplant open and scoop out the flesh.
(Scrape the flesh without tearing the skin; this enhances the smoky flavor of the dip.)
Mash the flesh until relatively smooth.

title: lemon pie
directions: Crumble wafers in bottom of bowl about 1 1/2 inches deep. Stand wafers around side of bowl.
Squeeze lemon juice into a cup. In large bowl, put Cool Whip and milk and stir until all is mixed, then pour in lemon juice gradually.
Fold in well.
Pour into crust and let stand several hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hillbilly pudding cake
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Cream white sugar and butter together.
Add eggs and crushed pineapple with juice.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and nuts together and sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and add boiling water and food coloring.
Mix thoroughly.
Cool.
Store in plastic bag at room temperature.

title: japanese fried rice
directions: Mix all together, season to taste and stir-fry until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until in peaks; fold in rest of ingredients. Put in well-greased pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes. May be served with whipped cream or ice cream.
Easy to make 2 batches at one time.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain.
Put in pan with other ingredients until done.
The longer your sauce simmers, the better it will be.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup with all ingredients, except water and can of mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 6 patties; place in shallow baking dish, uncovered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Spoon off fat.
Mix remaining soup, water and small can of mushrooms.
Pour over meat.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat
eggs,
Eagle
Brand
milk and sugar together real good, then mix in
condensed milk and vanilla extract.
Finish filling 1-gallon ice cream freezer with whole milk.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Separate sliced meat, set aside 5 to 7 pieces and dice the remaining slices.
Chop the green part of the scallions into 1/4-inch pieces; soften cream cheese.
Mix garlic salt into the cream cheese.
Add scallions and ham; mix.
Form into a ball.
Set atop 2 to 3 pieces of ham, then cover with the rest of the ham.

title: very good rolled sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350° to 375°.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Chill for 45 minutes.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface; cut out.
Place on cookie sheet which has been prepared with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool.

title: maple blueberry buckle
directions: First - In a small pot, cook fresh (or approximately 2 cups frozen blueberries), syrup, spices and cornstarch over medium to medium high heat until thickened.
Set aside.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam cooking spray.
Spread pecans and coconut in the pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix butter, sugar and cream cheese together.
Spoon gently over cake; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mary's baked macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil macaroni and drain.
Place layers of macaroni in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle the layers with grated cheese.
Beat the eggs, milk, salt and paprika until blended.
Pour this mixture over the macaroni.
Sprinkle the top with dry bread crumbs, dots of butter and grated cheese.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: creamed peas
directions: Cook peas according to package directions; drain.
In medium saucepan, melt butter; remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk and cream. Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil gently for 1 minute. Add peas; simmer 2 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spicy muffins
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and mound on muffin halves. On each muffin, place a slice of tomato and crisscross with 2 strips of sliced Cheddar cheese.
Broil for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Combine drained beans with remaining ingredients.
Add 2 hard-boiled eggs, chopped.
Chill.

title: potato soup
directions: Mash potatoes with masher.
Add condensed milk and butter. Cook until butter melts.
Don't boil.
Add parsley flakes.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Mix together the butter, crabmeat, mayonnaise, garlic salt and cheese and spread on muffins.
If you are preparing this ahead, place spread muffins on a baking tin.
Wrap and freeze.
When ready to serve, cut each half into quarters and broil until golden brown.
This makes about 48 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Stir together flour, brown sugar, nuts and oleo.
Spread evenly in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350°
oven for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 of crumbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine egg whites, sugar, strawberries and lemon juice.
With electric beater beat at high speed to stiff peaks about 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped whipping cream.
Spoon mixture over the crust and top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight.
Garnish with strawberries or whipped cream.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add flour and milk (may add more milk, if desired).
Stir constantly until mixture thickens.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Stir until melted.
(May use less cheese, if that is your taste.
I do.)
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: quick taco dip or sauce
directions: Blend briefly (3 seconds or so).

title: cranberry bread
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt into a large bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in eggs with orange rind and orange juice; blend mixture into flour mixture.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Fold in raisins, cranberries and nuts.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes or until done.

title: bachelor's roast
directions: Score roast in several places and fill scores with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Brown lightly on all sides in oil. Remove from pan and drain excess fat.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add onions, stuffing mix, cheese and seasonings.
Add eggs and margarine at once.
Blend with a fork. Form into balls.
Bake on greased sheet for 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen prior to baking.
Yields 7 dozen.
Great for parties.

title: chicken bake
directions: Drain mushrooms; save liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion.
Add seasonings and mushroom liquid.
Blend in chicken soup and stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring, until smooth and thick.
Mix rice, mushrooms, pimento and chopped chicken.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 1 minute. Add other ingredients. Mix to blend. Spread in a buttered pan, 8 x 8, to cool. Cut as desired. May be dropped by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and allowed to cool. Makes 36 cookies.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Put potatoes in large pot. Cover with water. Add salt; boil over high heat 10 to 15 minutes or until fork-tender. In skillet, fry bacon until crispy. Break into small pieces. Drain potatoes and let cool slightly. In large bowl, mix all ingredients well. Add the potatoes and mix well. Serve warm or cover and chill until ready to serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: traditional birthday cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Combine chocolate, sugar, milk and beaten egg in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until chocolate melts and mixture thickens; cool.
Stir shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add the eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Alternately add flour mixture and 2/3 cup milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat after each addition.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Bake in 2 paper lined or greased 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 25 minutes (more or less).
Remove from oven when cake separates from side of pan.

title: old-fashioned date-nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 clean, empty 1-pound coffee cans. In 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, bring milk to boil. Immediately remove from heat; add dates and let stand for 10 minutes.
In a large bowl stir flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and pecans to mix well.
In a medium-size bowl using wire whisk or fork, beat eggs lightly; stir in date-milk mixture and lemon extract until well blended.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture until just blended.
Pour batter into prepared cans; bake 50 to 55 minutes until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in cans on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove loaves from cans; cool completely.
Brush loaves with glaze.
Let stand for about 15 minutes until glaze is set.

title: oven stew
directions: Place all ingredients in roaster.
Bake for 4 hours at 325°. Serve over rice.

title: baked salmon and leeks
directions: Arrange fillets in well oiled baking dish.
In small skillet, lightly saute leeks and mushrooms in oil, about 4 minutes.
Add wine and stock; season lightly with salt and pepper to taste. Bring liquid to a boil, stir, reduce heat, cover and simmer several minutes until leeks are tender but still firm.
With slotted spoon, transfer vegetables to top of fish, cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Allow about 9 minutes per inch thickness of salmon.
Reduce pan liquid by half over high heat, whisking continuously.
Serve fish with sauce over cooked rice; garnish with snipped parsley.

title: impossible pumpkin pie(low calorie)
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth (1 minute in blender on high or 2 minutes with hand beater).
Pour into greased 9 x 1 1/4-inch or 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean (approximately 50 to 55 minutes).
Makes 8 servings.
One serving equals 120 calories or 1/2 bread, 1/2 milk and 1 fat exchange.

title: cranraspberry ring
directions: Cook the cranberries in 1 1/4 cups water until tender.
Remove free-floating loose skins.
Add sugar and cook an additional 5 minutes.
Pour the boiling mixture over jello and stir until dissolved.
Chill in the refrigerator until partially set.
Add celery, apples, nuts and salt.
Pour into a pretty mold and chill.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions; drain.
Rinse the pasta with cold water and drain.
Combine pasta and remaining ingredients, tossing well.
Serve immediately or if desired, chill.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Cook, season and drain string beans.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Mix string beans, sauteed pepper and onion, tomatoes, cornstarch and sugar.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Top with crushed 8 to 10 saltines.
Top with dots of butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: 5-cup dessert
directions: Mix all together.
Chill for several hours.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Dissolve
sugar in warm water.	Cool.
Add Kool-Aid and pineapple
juice.
Pour
in
ginger
ale.
May
also be frozen without ginger ale.
Place frozen block in punch bowl and pour ginger ale over to dissolve.

title: french bread(2 loaves)
directions: Sprinkle yeast into 1/2 cup water and stir until dissolved. Dissolve sugar and salt in 1 cup water.
Add shortening and yeast mixture; mix well.
Add flour and mix.
Work through dough with spoon 5 times at 10 minute intervals.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board and divide in half.
Shape into 2 balls and let rest for 10 minutes.
Roll into 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Place on baking sheet.
Score with 6 diagonal marks.
Cover with towel to raise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pie   lite
directions: Mix instant pudding with fat free milk.
Let it begin to thicken.
Then add 1/2 of the cool whip.
Blend together with a spoon.
Pour into the crust.
Let it get firm in the refrigerator. Before you serve it, add the rest of the cool whip to the top of the pie.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O; set aside to cool.
Add oil to cake mix; beat one minute.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing after each one.
Add Jell-O mixture to cake mix and beat for one minute. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rosamarina
directions: Cook rosamarina as directed on box and drain.
Dice mandarin oranges.
Drain oranges and pineapple and cook juices until thickened with the flour, salt, sugar and beaten eggs.
Cool juice mixture and add to rosamarina.
Add the fruit and refrigerate overnight.
Then add the Cool Whip and garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine butter and garlic; set aside.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper; stir well.
Dip each chicken breast in butter mixture and coat with bread crumb mixture.
Roll tightly, starting at narrow end, and secure with a toothpick. Arrange rolls in a shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with remaining butter and lemon juice.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: drunk chicken
directions: Combine grated cheese and parsley flakes in a bowl. Wash chicken and pat dry. Bread both sides with the cheese and parsley combination and fry in 1/4 cup oil until slightly brown (very slight). Combine soup combinations and add cooking wine.
Place chicken in baking dish and pour the soup mixture over it. Bake in a 350° oven until mixture bubbles. Great served over rice.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: In a bowl, combine cracker crumbs, pecans and sugar.
Add butter.
Mix well.
Set aside 1/2 cup of mixture.
Press remaining mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.

title: george strait's spanish rice
directions: In a skillet, brown rice in shortening.
Add the onion and bell pepper.
Stir, add salt, chili powder and tomatoes, including juice.
Add water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Remove both oven racks and cover with foil.
Turn oven at 350°.
Put egg whites into small mixing bowl.
Beat as for meringue, gradually adding sugar and vanilla.
Beat until forms very stiff peaks.
Remove beaters and carefully fold in chocolate chips and chopped pecans (optional).
Drop teaspoonfuls on foil racks.
Place racks in oven and turn oven off.
Leave overnight and do not open oven.
Remove and store in airtight container.

title: pat leonard's english muffin bread
directions: Heat liquids until warm.
Add yeast.
Stir into 3 cups flour and other ingredients.
Stir in enough of remaining flour as possible.
(Dough will be stiff and tacky.)
Spoon into 2 bread pans, greased and sprinkled with corn meal.
Let rise and bake until done.
Great when toasted.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Stir in sour cream.
Combine flour, baking powder and soda; add to creamed mixture, stir until combined.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and nuts over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Pick off bones and leave in large pieces.
Thaw broccoli in boiling water.
Drain well.
Spread thin layer of sauce in extra long pan.
Place next the broccoli over the sauce and next the chicken.
Toss wine and bread cubes together.
Drop over chicken.
Spread remainder sauce over the casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese croutons on top.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
I usually only bake 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 15 servings.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; put in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix crackers in with melted margarine.
Put on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.
If top begins to brown too quickly, cover lightly with foil.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fudge brownie pie(no crust)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 8-inch pie plate.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs; blend in sugar and margarine.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to margarine mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Pour into prepared pie plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until almost set.
(Pie will not test done in center.)
Cool; cut into wedges.
Serve topped with scoop of ice cream and Hot Fudge Sauce.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugars, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs in large bowl vigorously until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Mix together the flour, baking soda and salt; add to first mixture.
Add the chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix 1 egg, cake mix, butter and chopped nuts with hands and crumble in pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and pour over crumbled mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: deep-dish apple pie
directions: Arrange apple slices in a lightly greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Sprinkle over apples and dot with butter.
Top with pastry and bake	at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.	Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroons
directions: Cover cookie sheets with brown paper.
Using hands or food processor, soften almond paste.
Blend in order.
Drop by teaspoon or force through a cookie press onto covered cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Lay paper linings on very damp cloth. Let stand about 30 minutes after baking.
Let cool and peel off the macaroons.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine oil and Ranch mix.
Add dill weed, garlic powder and lemon pepper.
Pour over crackers; stir to coat.
Place in warm oven at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In deep 2-quart casserole dish, add macaroni.
In separate bowl, add beaten eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Cut cheese and butter into chunks and add to mixture. Pour mixture into dish of macaroni and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 to 45 minutes without a lid.

title: mexican sweet rice
directions: Cook rice according to manufacturers directions.
Heat all other ingredients (except marshmallows). Do not bring to boil. Add to cooked rice, stir well and add marshmallows.

title: turkey and chile casserole
directions: Combine broth, onion, and 1/2 teaspoon salt; heat to boiling. Stir in rice.
Cover and cook according to package directions. Stir chiles into sour cream with remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt. Layer 1/2 the rice, sour cream, turkey and cheese into 2-quart baking dish.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: soupy chicken sandwich
directions: Roast chickens until tender.
Allow them to cool.
Peel chicken from bone and shred into crock-pot.
Add cans of chicken, mushroom and celery soups, mix well.
Cook until hot.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Add sugar to cooked rice.
Cool.
Cut marshmallows in quarters.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and whipped cream to cooked rice.
Mix well.

title: brandied applesauce
directions: Peel, core and quarter the apples.
Place in water and cook over low heat until apples soften.
Stir occasionally, take from fire, add powdered sugar, cinnamon and brandy.
Simmer 5 minutes. Serve hot or cold.
Excellent with pork chops, chicken or potato pancakes.

title: drop sugar cookies(have ingredients at room temperature)
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream until fluffy butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg.
Combine dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Blend in 2 tablespoons milk. Drop by teaspoonfuls and flatten with bottom of glass that has been buttered and dipped in sugar.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until light golden brown around edges.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix milk, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in bread cubes, brown sugar and raisins.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine.
Bake at 350° until almost firm.

title: mushroom meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, beat egg with fork; add milk and bread crumbs. Stir to mix.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: lemon squares
directions: Beat butter and add flour and sugar.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Melt chips and wax.
Add Rice Krispies and coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in 9 x 3-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°; cool.
Beat together next 4 ingredients until creamy.
Fold in topping; spread over crust and chill 15 minutes.
Combine water and jello; dissolve.
Add frozen strawberries.
When mixture thickens, pour over cheese layer.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and cube avocados.
Mash and stir in garlic salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Add finely chopped onion and tomatoes, if desired, serve as a dip with tortilla chips or over burritos.

title: new england clam chowder with ukranian accents
directions: Dice onions finely.
Dice one potato fine and 3 potatoes into large chunks.
Heat 1 gallon pot on medium flame.
When hot, put in butter (or may use salt pork), then onion and stir until onions are clear.
Add potatoes, then drain the clam juice into the pot, reserving the clams.
Add water until potatoes are almost covered. Add pepper, parsley, rosemary and stir.
Add salt as needed. Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer; cover.
Cook 1 hour, stirring frequently.
When potato chunks are tender, add clams and milk.
Heat but do not boil.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin apple streusel muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Stir in apples.
Spoon batter into greased or paper lined muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Sprinkle Streusel Topping over batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: In skillet, simmer onion until yellow.
Add hamburger, cook until done.
Put all ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until heated through and bubbly.

title: diet custard
directions: Line a glass bowl with ladyfingers or sponge cake.
Pour frozen raspberries over; let juice soak in.
Make a custard and let cool and pour over raspberries and sponge cake.
Refrigerate and before serving, top with whipped cream.
Decorate with maraschino cherries.

title: stewed cabbage
directions: In large pan with
cover,
add	enough	water
to cover bottom of pan.
Add
sausage
and bacon.
Let cook until bacon is transparent.
Add garlic and onions.
Let cook until onions are transparent.
Wash cabbage	in
cold water.
Add cabbage a little at a time, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: cheesecake windyknowe
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar and add to crushed graham crackers. Add melted butter and mix.
Press into a 9-inch buttered spring-form pan.
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: shrimp and egg salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and add mayonnaise to desired taste. Garnish with green pepper rings.

title: shrimp-bacon bites
directions: Mix shrimp and garlic.
Pour chili sauce over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally, several hours.
Cut bacon slices into halves.
Cook bacon until limp and drain.
Wrap each shrimp in bacon pieces.
Secure with wooden pick.
Set oven on broil and/or 550°.
Broil with tops 2 to 3-inches from heat, until bacon is crisp.
(Shrimp may be substituted with oysters for oyster-bacon bites.)

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Heat electric skillet.
Add bacon drippings and heat 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir-fry until vegetables are tender.

title: chicken broccoli with rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, using chicken broth in place of water.
Saute onions and celery in oil.
Mix sauteed vegetables, cooked rice, broccoli, chicken and pepper.
Pour into a greased 4-quart casserole.
Combine cheese and soup in a small saucepan and heat over low flame until cheese melts.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Top with bread crumbs and bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: super meringue cookies
directions: Set oven to 350° before starting.
Line 2 cookie sheets with tinfoil.
In mixer, beat egg whites until thick and foamy. Gradually add sugar while mixer is in motion.
Beat until glossy, stiff peaks form.
Remove bowl from mixer and add vanilla, chocolate chips and walnuts, until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Shut oven off and put cookie sheets in oven. Leave in oven overnight or at least 3 to 4 hours.
Food coloring can be added after mixing, if desired.
Enjoy!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water with 1 stalk celery and 1/2 onion for about 1 hour.
Remove chicken from bones.
Grease casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces in bottom.
Pour about 1 cup cooking liquid into mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Melt butter in 1 cup cooking liquid and mix with stuffing.
Spread over chicken mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: weight watcher key lime pie
directions: Use speed set directions on jello box.
When slightly thickened, whisk in the yogurt.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Chill in refrigerator 2 hours.
Before serving, spread Cool Whip on top of pie.
Sprinkle zest of lemon on top.
Garnish with sliced lemon.

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour; measure with dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately to batter with buttermilk and vanilla.
Divide into 6 or 7 parts.
Use a well-floured board on which to roll out mixture or pat in well-greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 450° until slightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes.
Spread each layer with dried apple filling.
Do not put apples on the top layer.
Let stand in a covered container at least 12 hours before cutting.

title: grape pie
directions: Remove skins from grapes.
Save skins.
Put pulp into a saucepan without water and bring to a rolling boil.
While hot, run through colander to remove seed.
Mix pulp with skins.
Mix together sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice.
Then mix lightly through the grapes.
Pour grapes into pastry lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake until brown and juice is bubbling through crust slits.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: crispy oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine egg substitute and water in shallow dish, stir well. Combine cereal and next 6 ingredients in shallow dish; stir well. Place chicken pieces and flour in a large zip-top plastic bag, seal bag and shake until chicken is well coated.
Dip chicken in egg substitute mixture, dredge in cereal mixture.
Place chicken on rack of a broiler pan coated with vegetable cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and golden.
Yields 6 servings (248 calories).
Fat:
5.2 grams.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pinch off in bite size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: green rice
directions: Cook
broccoli and rice according to package directions (do not
use
quick
cooking
rice).
Saute
onions and green pepper in
stick of margarine.
Add cream of mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz blend.
Add cooked rice and broccoli and blend. Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mott's deliciously quick and easy cake
directions: Spray desired pans with cooking spray.

Prepare cake mix according to package directions with the following modifications: Add 1 tablespoon all-purpose flour to the dry mix and stir well. Substitute an equal amount of applesauce for the vegetable oil. Bake and cool as directed.
Frost cake with your choice of Betty Crocker light frosting.

title: peanut butter special treat
directions: Melt butter.
Add confectioners sugar, cocoa, peanut butter, milk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Roll into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: turkey crunch casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; stir soup into mayonnaise.
Toss with turkey mixture.
Put in 8 x 13-inch baking dish; sprinkle with noodles.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring the first four ingredients to boil 1 minute only. Remove from fire and add vanilla, peanut butter, oats and nuts. Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crumble cake into bite size pieces.
Mix milk, lemon juice, strawberries, vanilla and salt.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer, alternating cake with strawberry mixture.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: In a large microwave dish, cut cheese in small cubes.
Pour Ro-Tel over cheese and cover.
Microwave about 15 minutes; stir to keep from burning.
Serve while hot.
Can be melted in a crock-pot also.

title: gram farleigh's tapioca pudding
directions: Cover tapioca with water and soak for 6 hours or more.
Add milk and sugar to tapioca.
Cook until transparent.
Beat eggs. Add to pudding.
Cook until spoon is coated.
Add vanilla to taste.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops seasoned with Tony Chachere's Creole seasoning.	Spray or grease 13 x 9-inch casserole. Place raw rice in bottom of casserole and place chops on top of rice.

title: impossible mexican pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a 10-inch skillet until beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread beef mixture in pie plate.
Sprinkle with chilies and cheese.
Beat the remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed. Pour into pie plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted half way between center and edges comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with peppers and cheese, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut-caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine in skillet and add pecans and coconut.
Cook until golden brown.
Set aside.
Beat cheese until smooth; add condensed milk and beat a little longer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Take 1/4 of the cream mixture and place in each pie shell; then spread 1/4 of the caramel topping on each.
Next sprinkle 1/4 of the coconut mixture on top of each.
Repeat the process.
Freeze.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: baked empanada
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Cut in margarine using a pastry blender or dough cutter.
Add water and one egg. Blend until smooth.
Form into a ball and knead for a few minutes. Roll out on a floured board until you reach the desired thickness. Cut into rounds or squares and place a spoonful of filling (see below) in the middle.
Fold pastry and seal with the tine of a fork. Using the fork, prick the empanada twice on top.
Brush the tops with the egg yolk and milk mixture.
Place on a greased pan with oil and dusted with flour (or use a teflon baking pan) and bake for 30-45 minutes at 325° or until golden brown.

title: wild west dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Add tomatoes and green chilies; cut cheese in chunks and add to sausage mixture and melt. Serve in chafing dish with large corn chips.
Also good over baked potatoes.

title: golden cornmeal muffins*
directions: Sift together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Combine eggs, butter and milk.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten. Spoon batter into greased 3-inch muffin pan cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 12.

title: cherry blossom mold
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin in large bowl, stirring until dissolved.
Add yogurt and blend.
Add cherries and almonds. Chill until firm.
Enjoy!

title: scalloped cheese
directions: Butter enough slices of white (sandwich or other) bread to cover bottom of casserole dish; cut into 9 cubes each and lay in dish with buttered side down.
Cover with grated cheese over which is sprinkled a light coat of cayenne or red pepper.
Cover with another layer of buttered bread, cubed.
Add another layer of grated cheese lightly sprinkled with cayenne or red pepper.
Beat eggs; add milk to eggs.
Pour over the casserole.
Bake in 350° oven until solid in the center (about 30 minutes).

title: miracle whip scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, Miracle Whip or mayonnaise and cheese; mix lightly.
Place in oven dish and bake at 400° for 35 minutes. Drain and put in serving dish.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and salt together in a large bowl.
Add bran flakes and mix well.
Combine beaten eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and mix.
(Refrigerate for 6 weeks, if you wish and bake as needed.) Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: golden western pound cake
directions: Have eggs and margarine at room temperature.
Using mixer, cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Sift flour 3 times.
Add gradually to batter.
Add flavorings.
Bake in 10-inch greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 4 minutes and invert.
The best!

title: shipwreck
directions: In oblong casserole dish, layer first 6 ingredients in order given.
Dilute mushroom soup with water and pour evenly over casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil; bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add pecans.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in bowl.
Add nuts and coat thoroughly. Place on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: peanut chocolate clusters
directions: Melt chips and bark in microwave.
Mix together.
Add salted peanuts.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper and let set until dry, about 1 hour.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is still hot, punch holes with fork.
Mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour slowly over cake, allowing mixture to seep in.
Let cool.
Ice with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: brownie meltaways
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownies as directed on package, except stir coconut and nuts into dough.
Bake as directed; cool. Mix powdered sugar, 1/2 cup margarine and the vanilla.
Stir in milk, one teaspoon at a time, until of spreading consistency. Spread over brownies.
Refrigerate until topping is firm, about 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine the flour, sugar and baking powder; cut in margarine until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine Egg Beaters, milk and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened. Stir in blueberries.
Spoon into 12 (greased) or paper muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: quick taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet.
Add taco seasoning mix, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Place chips in medium size casserole dish.
Add meat mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: country chicken piccata
directions: In small bowl, combine milk and egg.
Combine flour, crushed corn flakes, salt and pepper.
Flatten each chicken breast half to about 1/4-inches thick by pounding between waxed paper.
Dip chicken into milk mixture, then into flour mixture, turning to coat.
In 10-inch skillet melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Add garlic and chicken.
Cook over medium heat, turning occasionally until golden brown, 5 to 6 minutes.
Place chicken on serving platter and keep warm.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter to dripping in pan.
Stir until butter melts; stir in lemon juice.
Add green onions and mushrooms.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally until heated through, 2 to 4 minutes.
Spoon over chicken. Garnish with lemon slices and parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mama mabel's sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes in pot.
While potatoes are boiling, set oven to 350°.
