When potatoes are cooked, run under cold water for a few minutes; this will help you to peel them without getting burned. Put potatoes in bowl and mash up real good.
Put butter in with potatoes, they should be just warm enough to melt your butter.

title: chicken rice goodness
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Arrange in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of shredded cheese.
Top with chicken.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon on cooked rice. Prepare a medium white sauce.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour; add milk all at once.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles. Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice, gently fold in sour crem and pour over chicken in casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining grated American cheese.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together.
Stir constantly.
Bring to a hard boil and boil 15 minutes pretty hard.
Take off heat.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter; beat until stiff.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch greased pan (grease with oleo).
Let cool and cut into small pieces.

title: mexican pizzas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Place tortillas on baking sheet. Top with hamburger mixture and cheese, leaving 1/2-inch of tortilla edge uncovered.
Bake at 400° until edges are crisp and golden and the cheese is melted, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Top with salsa if desired.

title: pink punch
directions: Make a little over 1 gallon mix ahead and add 7-Up just before serving.

title: noodles
directions: Add salt and baking powder to flour; rub shortening into flour.
Put eggs in cup; fill with canned milk.
Add to flour mix. Roll thin.
Put in broth.

title: polynesian dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, pineapple, sugar, oranges and half of the nuts in a bowl; mix well.
Spoon into serving dish. Chill until serving time.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut each breast fillet into 6 to 8 nuggets, about 1 1/2-inch squares.
Combine crumbs, cheese, Accent and salt.
Dip nuggets into margarine and roll into crumb mixture.
Place in single layers on foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: red cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs and make paste of cocoa, coloring and vanilla and blend into fat mixture.
Add salt, flour and buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar; add this while foaming and mix well.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until done.
Use 2 (8-inch) cake pans.
Split layers to make four.

title: herb bread(2 loaves)
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, 3 teaspoons salad dressing and mix well.
Heat buttermilk, water and shortening until warm.
Add to flour mix.
Add egg.
Blend well until moistened. Beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make firm dough.
Knead until smooth (5 to 10 minutes). Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm oven.
(Turn oven to 200° for 1 minute.
Turn off for 20.)
Punch dough down and divide in 2 parts.
Roll each part to 12 x 7-inch rectangle with large size roll up sealing edges and ends.
Place seam down on cookie sheet.
Make diagonal slits 2-inches apart on top.
Cover; let rise in warm oven 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with dressing mix.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat 3 cups milk.
Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and 1 cup milk and add to heated milk.
Let cool.
Then add egg yolks and cook until thick (you will need to use electric mixer while cooking to keep smooth).
When thickened, take off heat.
Add vanilla and pat of butter.
Pour into baked pie crust and use whites for meringue.

title: denver breakfast scramble
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook ham, mushrooms, onion and green pepper in oleo over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and dash of pepper.
Add to skillet.
Continue cooking over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 4 minutes or until eggs are cooked throughout, but are still glossy and moist.
Place cheese slices on top of mixture to melt for the last few minutes of cooking.

title: crab and shrimp salad
directions: Remove crusts from bread and butter.
Cut into cubes.
Place bread, eggs and onion in plastic bag.
Shake up and put in refrigerator overnight. Add celery, crab, shrimp and mayonnaise to bread mixture and chill. Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: cream cheese mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and
cut into cubes.
Cook until tender in boiling water.
Drain and place in a large bowl.
Add next five ingredients and beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust in a spring cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Mix the sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Pour on; bake for 5 minutes at 375°.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill until quite firm.
Whip until light and foamy.
Mash cream cheese and fold into pineapple.
Fold this mixture into whipped gelatin. Fold in the Dream Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes, dice, cook and drain.
Cook onion and celery together, drain.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Next day, bring to boil in same water.
Cut bacon into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Add all ingredients to beans and pour into ceramic pan or bean pot.
Bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook
squash and onions;
drain.
Combine soup and sour cream and stir in carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onions. Combine stuffing
mix and butter.
Spread half in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour
vegetables over.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.	Serves 8.

title: kahlua
directions: Make simple syrup by boiling sugar and water for 5 minutes. While hot; add instant coffee.
Let cool.
Put into gallon jug. Add liquor and vanilla beans.
Let stand 2 weeks.
Note:
Keep vanilla beans and add 1 fresh bean for next brew.

title: pineapple casserole(yields 4 servings)
directions: Place drained pineapple chunks in a greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish/pan.
In a small bowl, mix sugar and flour. Sprinkle over pineapple.
Layer grated cheese, then cracker crumbs.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: apple-pineapple slaw
directions: Combine all above ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Add eggs to milk.
Stir. Then add extract, juice and rind. Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar slowly and then salt. Pour filling into baked pie shell.
Top with egg whites.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: cold yellow squash soup
directions: Boil squash and onion in bouillon until tender.
Puree in blender.
Add cream cheese, curry powder, seasoned salt, garlic salt and red pepper to taste.
Continue blending until frothy and well mixed.
Serve cold with garnish of parsley and sour cream, if desired.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk to beaten egg.
Dip cleaned shrimp into mixture.
Take shrimp out of egg and milk mixture.
Drop and wrap shrimp in flour.
Shake excess flour from shrimp.
Fry shrimp in medium hot grease until golden brown.
Serve hot!

title: yorkser pudding
directions: Mix everything together until smooth.
Add a little water to mixture until it looks like heavy cream.
Heat oven to 450°.
Put 1 teaspoon meat drippings into each muffin tin hole.
Heat drippings in oven until it starts to smoke.
Pour batter into tins.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 5 to 9.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs. Pour two cups of batter into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan; bake 15 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Jell the Jell-O and water about 20 minutes in freezer.
Beat until fluffy and add remaining ingredients.
Cut into squares.

title: banana punch
directions: Puree banana in blender along with orange juice and lemonade. Mix with remaining ingredients, stirring until sugar is dissolved.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind vegetables, sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight. Rinse and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Boil 3 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: pasta salad-peggy's way
directions: Boil pasta in large pan with approximately 1 tablespoon salt until tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together all other ingredients except ham and bacon.
Then mix in cooled pasta.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Stir several times. Add ham and bacon the next morning and return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes with celery and onion.
Combine ranch mix, mayonnaise and water.
Add this to potatoes and toss.
Chill.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all ingredients
together.
Cook
and stir until it boils. Cook for 20
minutes or more until tender.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Very good with meats and vegetables.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer all ingredients.
Do not stir.
Save some bacon and cheese for topping.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar and pour on top of layered salad.
Garnish with bacon and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight, covered with Saran Wrap.
When ready to serve, mix lightly.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Drain artichokes and chop.
Mix together other ingredients. Pour into 2 small souffle dishes and bake until golden and bubbly in 350° oven.
Great on crackers.

title: shanghai beef
directions: Saute beef in oil in large skillet until browned (about 5 minutes).
Add cornstarch and blend well.
Add broth, water chestnuts, red pepper, soy sauce, onions and black pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Stir in rice and remove from heat. Let stand about 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender. Add onion. Heat soup in 1/2 cup water in saucepan. Alternate layers of squash, cheese, soup and crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix all in bowl, except confectioners sugar.
Roll into teaspoon-size balls.
Roll each ball in confectioners sugar. Store in tight containers.

title: north carolina grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Butter a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish or shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In a large bowl, beat eggs just until yolks and whites are blended.
Stir in milk and corn syrup until blended.
In a small bowl, stir together sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg until well mixed.
Add to egg mixture and stir until blended.
Stir in butter.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 375° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 dozen muffins.

title: dewberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch or flour, add salt; sprinkle over fruit in pastry-lined pie pan, or if desired, mix dry ingredients with fruit before putting fruit in pie shell.
Dot with butter or margarine and adjust top crust.
Cut slits in top crust.
If Crumb Topping is used instead of top crust, you may omit the tablespoon of butter to dot fruit.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken meal on the grill
directions: Triple aluminum foil (or x2 if using heavy duty foil) to approximate size of 16-inches, for chosen number of chicken dinners (each leg and thigh quarter).
Place chicken and all ingredients in center of the foil.
Again triple aluminum foil as instructed and place on top of the chicken meal.
Roll towards the meal, leaving creased edges on all four sides.

title: fluff salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and dry Jell-O together.
Add orange sections.
Mix and serve.

title: fool's toffee
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and lightly butter.
Lay saltine crackers on foil.
Melt butter and brown sugar over medium-high heat.
Bring to boil and boil for 4 minutes.
Spread over crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes in 375° oven.
Remove from oven and pour chocolate chips over.
Soften and spread.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Cool in refrigerator.
When cool, break into pieces.
Will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll in nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: white bread(2 loaves)
directions: Put in a large bowl 3 cups of flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Into small saucepan put warm water and shortening.
Let stand a few minutes.
Then add to flour mixture and beat for 2 minutes with electric mixer.

title: rawlie's raisin sauce for ham
directions: Boil raisins in water for 20 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into boiling raisins, stirring constantly for 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour over sliced ham and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Peel meat
off
bones
in
thin
strips.
In
a greased baking dish, layer some chicken on bottom, then some Stove Top bread crumbs,
then chicken;
continue layering until chicken is used up and
a
few
bread crumbs are left.
Combine water with the cream of mushroom soup and the seasoning packet from Stove Top. Pour
this
over
the
layers
in the baking dish; garnish with the
rest
of the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until browned and done.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package and let cool completely. Crumble half of cake in the bottom of a punch bowl.
Then begin to layer: 1/2 pudding, 2 to 3 bananas, pineapple, fruit pie filling, 1/2 Cool Whip and nuts.
Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions and pepper; cook until tender. Add tomato sauce and paste; stir.
Mix cornmeal, milk, egg, corn, olives, cheese, garlic, salt, chili powder, cumin and oregano and stir into meat and sauce mixture; stir well.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Puree tomatoes and tomato paste.
Add seasonings.
Brown beef and onions.
Stir in 1/2 of spaghetti sauce mix.
Spoon cottage cheese evenly over meat.
Arrange uncooked noodles on top. Sprinkle with remaining spaghetti sauce mix.
Pour tomato mixture over all; press down to be sure all noodles are moistened.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella; simmer 5 more minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well. Put ungreased casserole dish Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. 5	minutes before time. Remove meat loaf drain grease top with mixture of equal amounts
ketchup, mustard, lemon juice and brown sugar. Put back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the first 6 ingredients in the order shown.
Spread the mayonnaise over top of layers.
Cover with Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle bacon over top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dill dip(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy with raw vegetables.

title: cheese ring
directions: Beat Parmesan cheese, Miracle Whip and cream cheese until creamy; add bacon and green onion tops.
Chill overnight.
Shape into a wreath, heart or a ball with a spatula.
Top with dry parsley flakes.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs slightly, then beat in sugar, salt, vanilla, nutmeg and milk.
Pour into crust and bake 40 minutes.

title: hot chicken bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and top with Rice Krispies.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Celery will be crisp.

title: refrigerator sweet pickles
directions: Prepare brine, using sugar and vinegar.
Stir until dissolved on low heat.
Let stand 1 hour.
Soak vegetables for 2 hours in salt.
Drain juice.
Pour brine over vegetables.
Put in jars and refrigerate.
Ready to eat in 2 to 3 days.
Will keep for 3 months in refrigerator.

title: pie crust
directions: Stir all together.
Roll between 2 pieces of wax paper.

title: jello salad
directions: Let cream cheese soften and mix with mayonnaise.
Mix water and Jell-O.
Let it begin to gel.
Add cream cheese mixture, pineapple, and other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add salad dressing.
Blend thoroughly. Add water and vanilla gradually.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into two 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan until done, approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: 5-minute brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt the chocolate and butter.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and milk in the top of a double boiler.
Add nuts and spoon onto a greased pan.
Put the pan in the freezer overnight.
Melt chocolate in the microwave; dip the caramel mounds and return to the greased pan until it hardens.

title: cherry cheese cake(quick and easy)
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar together then pour over a graham cracker crust.
Top with cherries.
Refrigerate one to two hours

title: cucumber party sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing mix. Spread on bread. Top with cucumber slices. Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Add broccoli to other ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Cook in a well greased 9 x 12-inch pan at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add mashed bananas and remaining ingredients.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour in loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken, remove bones and put in a casserole dish. In same pot as chicken was boiled, mix broth and soup; pour over chicken.
Add flour to melted margarine (in same boiling pot). Then slowly add milk to blend.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until browned on top.

title: honey bread
directions: Mix Crisco with honey.
Mix dry ingredients, then fold into Crisco mixture.
Add water gradually.
Roll out or pat into shape on greased cookie sheet.
Score into squares if desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together and add rest of ingredients. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350°
for 40 minutes or until set.

title: pizza quiche
directions: Place pie crust in a 9-inch quiche pan.
Heat oven to 400°. Layer cheese in pie crust.
Top with pepperoni and mushrooms.
In medium bowl, combine milk, eggs, seasoning and garlic; beat well. Pour egg mixture over mushrooms.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Meanwhile, simmer spaghetti sauce over low heat.
Cut quiche into pie slices and spoon sauce over each slice.

title: delicious fresh string beans
directions: Steam beans 15 to 20 minutes.
In a skillet place olive oil. Heat 2 minutes.
Add chopped onion.
Saute until onions are clear. Add beans, bouillon and garlic powder.
Stir for 2 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream peanut butter, shortening and brown sugar in large bowl.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Add egg.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed; mix just until blended.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Coat pecans and place one layer of pecans on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like fine meal.
Press firmly in 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until edges are slightly browned.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Mash 1/2 box of strawberries.
Add sugar and cornstarch mixed in a little water and cook together until thickened.
Set in refrigerator to cool.
Take other 1/2 box of strawberries and cut in halves or quarters and cool.
Put cut up berries in shell and then the berry mixture on top.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: marshmallow roll
directions: Melt butter and chocolate; beat egg.
Add salt.
Fold egg into chocolate mixture.
Add nuts, sugar and marshmallows.
Divide into two parts.
Roll in wax paper.
Roll in coconut or ground nuts.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400° and grease a pie plate with shortening.
Put onions in skillet and add ground beef and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 10 minutes (until brown).
Drain off fat and spread beef mixture in pie plate.
Put milk, eggs and baking mix in blender and blend on high 15 seconds.
Pour blender mixture over beef mixture in pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes longer.
Cool five minutes on wire rack.
Serves 6.

title: uncooked peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine on low; stir constantly. Remove from heat; add egg, sugar and milk.
Mix together with your hands until smooth.
Place in 8 x 8-inch buttered pan for thick fudge.
Place in 15 x 10-inch buttered pan for thinner fudge.
I prefer the thinner.
Refrigerate.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix taco seasoning, creamed corn and beans with
juice
into
hamburger.
Crumble chips in bottom of	a
long
casserole dish (any amount you like). Pour meat mixture over chips and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Then sprinkle with
shredded
cheese over top and heat until cheese melts. Suggestion:
Serve with sour cream or mild or hot taco sauce.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Mix everything, except noodles and flavor pack.
Crumble noodles.

title: liver dumplings
directions: Grind onion, parsley and liver together.
Put flour into mixing bowl.
Add ground liver, onion and parsley, seasoning and eggs and mix with milk like any other batter.
Put 3 quarts of water in a pan and 2 tablespoons salt, heat to boiling.
Put some of the batter on a plate.
When water boils, take a table knife, dip in hot water and cut little slivers of batter off plate.
Let drop into hot water and occasionally dip knife in hot water to keep dough from sticking.
Keep on boiling until you have all the batter scraped in.
Cook a minute or two, drain in colander.
Pour a cup of cold water over and drain.
After finished draining, put in a bowl.
Heat a tablespoon of lard or other shortening (chicken fat is good).
Pour over dumplings and mix.
Now they are ready to serve.

title: yellow cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until fluffy. Stir in eggs, milk and remaining ingredients.
Bake in three 9-inch round pans or a 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mock turkey loaf
directions: Melt cheese in milk.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Can be topped with mushroom soup after baking.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and 5 tablespoons sugar; work flour, vanilla and nuts into creamed mixture.
Form into desired shape.
Cook on ungreased baking sheet at 325° to 355° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: cookie and pudding pie
directions: Place cookies on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Pour cold milk into bowl.
Add ice cream and beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Add pudding mix; beat again until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Let it stand 3 minutes.
Pour pudding into cookie-lined pie plate.
Put pie into refrigerator to chill until set, about 3 hours.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°. Cover and cook another 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes. Cool.
Yield: 8 servings.
Carbohydrate 20 g, protein 2 g, fat 5 g, calories 188; 1/8 piece pie = 1 bread starch exchange, 1/2 fruit exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: school day cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Grease a large baking sheet. In a large bowl cream together the shortening and sugar. Add the eggs and beat well. Add the orange juice, rind and vanilla; beat until mixed. In medium bowl, sift together the flour, salt and baking soda. Add to the creamed mixture and beat well. Stir in the oats, dates, and walnuts. Drop from a teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on a rack. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Soften margarine to room temperature.
Beat in eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add baking powder to flour and sift together slowly into margarine mixture.
Roll out dough on floured board and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until brown as desired.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: dot's dip
directions: Mix and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Right before serving, mince small cucumber and mix well.
Serve with vegetables.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place ingredients in layers in this order:
asparagus spears, drained, chopped eggs (sprinkle with salt and pepper), cracker crumbs, grated cheese, enough soup to make moist and some juice from asparagus.
End with cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Just before done, sprinkle top with more cheese.
Serves 6.

title: microwave sticky buns
directions: In an 8-inch round microwave pan, combine the dark brown sugar, butter and water.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 minute.
Stir in nuts.
Cut each of the 10 biscuits into quarters and stir into brown sugar mixture to coat.
Push to sides and insert glass to form a ring mold.
Cook, uncovered, 2 minutes and 30 seconds, until biscuits are firm and not doughy.
Let stand two minutes. Remove glass and invert onto serving plate.
Best when served warm.

title: peach dijon pork chops
directions: Heat grill. In small saucepan, combine preserves, mustard, soy sauce and marjoram; mix well. Cook over low heat until preserves are melted, stirring frequently.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, rinse and drain and add pickles, eggs, onion, celery seed, salt and pepper and tomato.
Add salad dressing to ingredients, mix and serve chilled.

title: flame cake
directions: 1. Mix together cocoa with red food color.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat in microwave and serve warm with any chips.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: In blender or small bowl for mixer, combine sugar, dry mustard, salt, white wine vinegar and onion.
Gradually incorporate salad oil as you would for mayonnaise.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups dressing.

title: coconut-crunch torte
directions: Combine crumbs, coconut and nutmeats.
Beat whites with salt and vanilla until foamy; gradually add sugar and beat until whites form stiff peaks.
Fold in graham cracker mixture.
Spread in well-greased pie plate and bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes. Cool.
Cut in wedges and top with ice cream.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese and Cheddar cheese come to room temperature. Mix cheeses, gradually adding dressing mix, a little at a time until entire package is used.
If too sticky, refrigerate or place in freezer 30 to 45 minutes.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans. Makes a large ball so recipe can be cut in half.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 375° until brown, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange pound cake
directions: Grate orange peel.
Chop cranberries in blender and mix with peel.
Mix cake mix according to directions, except substitute orange juice for water.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add cranberry mixture and mix well. Grease and flour Bundt pan using butter and flour.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top cake when done with powdered sugar.

title: barbra's shrimp soup
directions: Saute onion, carrot, thyme, bay leaf, parsley and celery in 2 tablespoons butter until browned.
Shell and devein shrimp.
Cook covered in 1 cup of broth and wine for 5 minutes.
Strain.
Combine remaining broth with sauteed vegetables and bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Cook rice until tender.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Add eggs and bananas.
Stir about 5 minutes.
Add sour milk.
(To make sour milk, add 1 tablespoon vinegar to milk.)
Sift dry ingredients and beat well. Add flavoring.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 layer pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost and serve.

title: almond delight
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, almonds, coconut and flour.
Place in a shallow baking pan; bake at 325° until brown, about 30 minutes, stirring often so it will brown evenly.
Place 1/2 of this mixture in baking dish.
Combine pudding mix and milk; beat according to package directions.
Fold dessert topping into pudding mixture and spread over the crumb mixture in dish.
Top with remaining crumbs and chill.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: In skillet brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain off fat. Sprinkle meat with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Place 1 can of green chilies, cut in half crosswise and seeded, over meat. Combine beaten eggs, milk, flour, salt, several dashes of bottled hot pepper sauce and dash of pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over chili mixture.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted just off center comes out clean.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.
Serves 6.

title: banana-carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12 cup muffin tin.
Grate carrots.
Mash bananas.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy. Add egg and beat well.
Stir in bananas.
In a small bowl, mix together oat bran, wheat germ, flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add to banana mixture.
Add carrots, vanilla and nuts carefully.
Fill muffin tin and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until a cake tester comes out clean.

title: cream puffs
directions: Pour boiling water over oleo in saucepan.
Bring to boil and stir until oleo melts.
Add flour all at once and stir with wooden spoon until mixture leaves the side of pan and forms ball.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add eggs one at a time, beating smooth. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto greased sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes and then reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 to 40 additional minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls in a mug with boiling water.
Stir and serve with a cinnamon stick for garnish.

title: sugar coated nuts
directions: Put all ingredients together and cook until it turns to sugar (all liquid will cook out and form soft balls of sugar).
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Drain and add spices.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Cut tomatoes, apples, onions and peppers into small pieces. Combine with remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 4 hours or until thick.
Put in jars and seal.

title: fluffy cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in pudding.
Mix and add fruit filling.
When the mixture is starting to set, add whipped topping.
Pour into bowl and chill until set.

title: meat turnovers
directions: Cut shortening into sifted flour, baking powder and 2 teaspoons salt in bowl.
Add egg and water, tossing lightly to form a soft dough.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken and debone.
In a large bowl combine chicken, green chilies, onion and 1/4 cup of cheese. Mix well.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning mix together.

title: party punch
directions: Combine the chilled ingredients.
Pour into a medium punch bowl with a frozen ice ring.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Sprinkle salt over vegetables and cover with water.
Let stand 4 hours.
Squeeze out all water or run through colander.
Drain well.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Let come to a boil.
Add cucumbers, onion and pepper.
Simmer 25 minutes, then can.

title: rolls
directions: Put potatoes through sieve to avoid lumps in potatoes.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough (about 5 cups).
Let rise until double in size.
Make into rolls and bake in a 375° oven.
This will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Combine sugar, dates, eggs, shortening, vanilla and salt.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
When cool, add 3 cups Rice Krispies and 1/2 cup nuts.
Makes into balls and roll in chopped coconut.

title: salmon in apricot sauce
directions: Preheat broiler for 10 minutes.
Place salmon steaks on broiler pan.
Place pan 4 to 5 inches from source of heat and broil for 10 minutes per side.
Meanwhile, combine brown sugar, cornstarch and peel in a medium size saucepan.
Blend juice and apricots.
Stir into dry mix.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring until it thickens.
Stir in onion and vinegar.
Spoon over salmon steaks during last 2 minutes of broiling.
Serve.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: "banana split dessert"
directions: For Crust:
Combine vanilla wafers and melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13 pan.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in pot and drain.
Brown meat in saucepan; drain oil.
Mix all ingredients.
Combine meat also in spaghetti pot.
Stir occasionally.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cheese, if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a large loaf pan. Bake in a 425° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: low-fat meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine bread crumbs, sage, pepper, egg whites, onion, garlic and milk. Add beef and mix.
Place in a shallow baking pan. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and carefully drain fat from pan. Combine tomato sauce, mustard and brown sugar. Spread over meat loaf and bake 15 minutes more. Makes 8 servings.

title: ranch meat loaf
directions: Pour over the top of the meat loaf and bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: american meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1/4 cup catsup.
Shape into loaf.
Put in baking pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Allow meat loaf to cool for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: two minute dumplings
directions: Break the egg into a measuring cup.
Add milk to egg to make 1/2 cup.
Beat well; stir slowly into sifted dry ingredients.
Add more milk, if necessary, but keep batter stiff.
Drop into boiling stock with spoon dipped in stock.
Cover; simmer for 2 minutes. Turn dumplings.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Serve at once.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Divide in half and form large rolls.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Bake cake; let cool.
Then spoon other mixture over cake.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all together in one bowl by hand.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baked duck
directions: Tie legs of duck together.
Pierce duck all over in fat areas around thighs and legs.
Place on rack of roasting pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste every 30 minutes with honey glaze. Remove fat from pan as it bakes with a bulb baster, before each basting of ducks.
Ducks are done when legs move easily and juice is clear when skin is pricked.

title: olive cheese spread
directions: Mix all together for spread on Ritz crackers, Triscuits, etc. Keeps long time in refrigerator.

title: calipso marinade
directions: Blend well in blender.
Pour over steaks and let set about 1 hour.
Drain and grill steaks to taste.

title: enchilada casserole(lo-cal)
directions: Cook beef and onion in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until browned, stirring to crumble. Drain well. Stir tomato sauce and next 5 ingredients into mixture. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: overnight french toast
directions: The day before, melt together in large heavy pan butter.
Add apple slices and cook until tender.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and cinnamon to apples.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange bread slices in 1 layer on top of the apples.
In medium bowl, beat eggs, milk and almond extract.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake until brown on top at 375° (about 35 minutes).

title: brenda's banana bread
directions: To make sour milk, stir 1 tablespoon white vinegar into one cup whole milk.
Let sit for 20 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk and sour cream.
Mix jello and water with pie glazing.
Add berries.
I chop some of the berries and add while frozen.
Put on cake layers, jello and pudding.
Repeat. Top with Cool Whip.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening in large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add mixture with flour.
Stir 1/2 cup M&M's.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Decorate top with remaining candy.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Some cracking may occur.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs; beat 1 minute at medium speed of electric mixer.
Combine next 5 ingredients; add to pumpkin mixture.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed of electric mixer. Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour batter into three greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers and on top of cake.

title: one crust raisin pie
directions: Put the sugar, raisins and water in saucepan and bring to boil. Mix the cream, salt, cornstarch and beaten egg yolks, add to boiling mixture. Cook until thick. Pour into baked pie crust. Beat egg whites until stiff. Put on top and bake until brown.

title: old fashioned fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease Bundt pan heavily, then spray with
Pam.	Cut
up
fruit.
Combine
in
large bowl the fruit, coconut,
pecans
and 1/2 cup flour;
mix well, coating each piece with
flour.
In
another	bowl, beat eggs and add sugar, 1
cup flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour over the fruit mixture; blend together.
Turn batter into prepared pan. Bake for 1	hour and
40 minutes, or until the top is glossy. Cool in pan
for
10 minutes.
Turn out and finish cooling on wire rack.
Wrap in aluminum foil; store in airtight container for 2
to
weeks before
serving.
Keeps
well for several months.

title: *meat pita
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add hamburg.
Brown meat, then add tomato paste or sauce.
Add rest of the ingredients, except eggs. Cook partially and let cool.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits thoroughly, saving the peach and pineapple juice. Cook until clear
cups juice, sugar, cornstarch and corn syrup.
Add 5
tablespoons apricot Jell-O to hot mixture. Cool and pour over
fruit.
Pretty
served
in
a
clear glass bowl.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Piece
together
crescent
rolls
in a pie pan.
Thinly slice zucchini,
leaving	skins
on;
saute it with onion and butter for 15 minutes.
Add remaining garlic powder, oregano, basil and parsley.
Beat
eggs
in
a bowl and add cheese. Combine all in the pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 of cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: chunky apple pecan cake(great christmas cake)
directions: Butter and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan (or spray).
Sift flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat oil, melted oleo, eggs, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Stir in dry ingredients. Batter will be very thick.
Fold in apples, pecans, raisins and halved cherries.
Spoon into pan and smooth over with spoon.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Let cool completely in pan.
Invert pan onto platter.

title: salmon cabbage rolls
directions: In a small mixing bowl combine egg, onion, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add salmon and rice.
Mix well.
Immerse cabbage leaves in boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes or until limp; drain.
Remove heavy center rib of leaves, keeping each leaf in one piece.
Place 1/4 of the salmon mixture on each leaf.
Fold sides and ends over filling.
Place cabbage rolls, seam side down, in individual serving dish.
For make-ahead, seal and chill for 3 to 24 hours.

title: fried eggplant or green tomatoes
directions: Slice large green tomatoes into thick slices.
Peel and cut eggplants into square sticks.
Salt and pepper eggplants; let drain in colander for 1/2 hour.
Dredge eggplant sticks or tomatoes in flour, then dip in egg wash.
Roll in bread crumbs; deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: super-natural bran muffins
directions: In a 2 to 3-quart container or bowl with a cover, stir together bran and water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, in another large bowl, combine the oil, sugar and honey and mix well. Beat the eggs into the oil mixture, add and mix in the buttermilk.
Mix the oil mixture into the bran mixture.
In another bowl, combine and mix flour, soda, salt and granola. Slowly blend these ingredients into bran mixture. Cover and refrigerate the batter for several hours or overnight.

Spoon batter into greased muffin tins, fill 2/3 full. Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 22 to 25 minutes or until brown and a toothpick inserted in the center of a muffin comes out clean. Cool before removing from pans.
The remaining batter may be used as needed and will keep refrigerated, tightly sealed for 4 weeks.

title: peanut butter topper
directions: Spread bagel with peanut butter.
Top with raisins, banana and sunflowers.

title: candied grapefruit peel
directions: Using point of knife, score grapefruit peel in 4 lengthwise sections.
If peel is quite thick, cut away some of the membrane. Cut peel into 1/4-inch strips.
Place cut peel in large saucepan, cover with cold water and bring to boiling.
Boil 20 minutes; drain.
Repeat twice more, using fresh cold water each time. Drain thoroughly.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in greased casserole dish.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant. Cook until tender; drain, then add butter, salt, pepper, milk and well beaten eggs. Add onions and cracker crumbs. Pour in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake for 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: black walnut cake(serves 24)
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given, beating well after each egg. Stir in nuts. Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from stem of peppers; remove all seeds and membranes.
Wash inside and outside.
Cook peppers in the boiling, salted water 5 minutes; drain.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in medium skillet until onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in salt, rice, 1 cup of tomato sauce, corn and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat through.

title: quick pork chop casserole
directions: Mix rice and soup in a casserole.
Place pork chops on top. Place in microwave.
Cook for 20 minutes at 70 (Bake on my microwave).
You may have to adjust time to power level according to your microwave oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except almonds, butter and crackers.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Mix crumbs and butter and put on top.
Put almonds on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: old-fashioned caramel cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar slowly and cream together.
Add beaten eggs; add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake in two well-greased 8-inch layer cake pans for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: oven apple butter
directions: Cook apples in oven until done.
Mash.
Add sugar and vinegar. Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.
Add cinnamon.

title: taco dip
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Cream together the cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix in taco seasoning mix.
Spread in pan.
Top with cut up lettuce, tomatoes, onion and taco cheese. Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hamburg balls
directions: Wash rice thoroughly.
Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into small balls and brown the balls in a frypan with garlic.
Pour sauce over them and cook slowly for about an hour.

title: barley soup(ukrainian)
directions: Wash the pearl barley; cook in a large amount of lightly salted boiling water until tender.
Meanwhile, cook the onion in the butter until lightly wilted.
Add the vegetables, mushrooms and soup stock.
Simmer until the vegetables are done.
Strain the cooked barley and add to the soup.
Stir in the sour cream and bring to a boil.
Season to taste with the salt and pepper. Garnish with the dill or parsley.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Wash peppers, towel dry, cut in halves.
Clean inside and put aside.
Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Mix well; spoon mixture in hollow section of peppers, forming rounded half. Place in casserole dish and pour tomato sauce over peppers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Last 5 minutes, top with shredded cheese.

title: sweet cheese dip
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, marshmallow cream, milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Beat until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups of dip.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Place vegetables and broth in saucepan.
Boil, reduce heat and cook until tender.
Mix milk, cornstarch, salt, pepper and thyme; add to vegetables.
Cook constantly until it begins to boil; remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted.

title: pink shrimp sauce with cream
directions: Clean shrimp and cut in 1/2 lengthwise.
Put olive oil and chopped garlic in a saucepan; cook on medium heat, stirring until pale gold.

title: swedish pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 9-inch pie tin.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: meat and vegetable casserole
directions: Melt fat in skillet, add chopped onion, pepper and garlic; cook until tender.
Add seasoned ground meat, to which eggs have been added.
Brown lightly.
Sprinkle casserole with crumbs.
Add half meat mixture, half the corn, half tomatoes and repeat. Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: to make eagle brand milk
directions: Mix well.
If sugar doesn't dissolve, put on low heat and warm it up a little until sugar is dissolved.

title: sue's applesauce drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and blend in eggs and applesauce. Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg
to creamed mixture. Blend in raisins and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Put into greased and floured bread pans (8 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/2-inch). Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: vegetable frittata
directions: In a large skillet, heat olive oil and saute onion for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini
and red pepper and saute for 5 minutes or until soft.
Stir in potatoes and olives.
Cool.

title: lep cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Let	rise
overnight.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes
500 to 600 cookies.
Will keep a year if stored in airtight containers.

title: blender quiche
directions: Put all ingredients except meat and cheese in blender for a few seconds. Pour into 9-inch greased pie pan. Add meat and cheese and push down into egg mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes until eggs slightly brown. Let set 10 minutes before cutting.

title: fruit crepes
directions: Stir all this together.
I usually use a whipping wand, but can be mixed by hand.
Let rest for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add milk and stir.
Sift flour and cocoa; add to mixture.
Stir well and pour into a 9-inch cake pan.

title: the best cheesecake
directions: Mix Philadelphia cream cheese and powdered sugar together. Spread over crust.
Mix pudding, milk and 1/2 of Cool Whip together; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with other 1/2 of Cool Whip and grated Hershey chocolate bars.

title: baked beans
directions: Place all beans in a large casserole.
Chop bacon and fry in large skillet.
Do not drain bacon grease.
When bacon is brown, add onion rings.
Fry until tender.
Then add brown sugar, vinegar, garlic powder and dry mustard.
Stir and simmer for a few minutes.
Add all to beans and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Layer chicken, carrots, sliced potatoes, peas and eggs into large casserole dish.
In saucepan, heat chicken soup, mushroom soup and chicken broth and pour over layers.
Mix together flour and butter; add milk.
Mix and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Brown at 350° in jelly roll pan or 2 pizza pans.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° (no more) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine meat, onion, green pepper and garlic in saucepan. Cook and stir until onions are limp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili that mom makes
directions: Mix ingredients in a pot.
Stir.
Cook for 25 minutes on the stove.
Serve with crackers (as many as you like).
"The best chili ever for my family."

title: steamed persimmon pudding
directions: Press persimmons through sieve.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart greased top of double boiler.
Put cover on tight and steam for 2 hours without removing cover.
Serve warm with a spoonful of whipped topping.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix all together and simmer for 1 hour.

title: party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill in refrigerator and serve with vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Toss and serve.
No need to let set.
You can put bananas in Fruit Fresh or lemon juice to keep them from turning brown. Yields 4 quarts.

title: italian pork chops mozzarella
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat chops with coating mix as directed on package.
Discard any remaining coating mix.
Place chops in 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes or until cooked through.
Top chops with spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Bake an additional 10 minutes or until sauce is warm and cheese is melted.

title: ralphie's hot mac cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Boil macaroni according to directions on box; drain. Mix all ingredients together, except Colby cheese. Pour into a baking dish and top with Colby cheese. Bake in oven until golden brown.

title: katy's favorite dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes covered, then 5 minutes uncovered.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a separate bowl, mix cream cheese and light cream.
Mix with beater 2 minutes until smooth.
Blend the 2 mixes together. Pour in baking pans that can be placed in warm water to bake. Bake at 325°
for 1 hour or until set as custard.
Cool and serve. Serves 12.

title: rich and fluffy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate squares with butter over hot water.
Beat eggs until foamy; gradually add sugar.
Blend in chocolate mixture; stir in flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Add potatoes and onion. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until potatoes are tender in a large skillet.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add onions, garlic, salt and pepper. Make chicken broth with 3 cubes of chicken bouillon.
Cut up tomatoes from the can.
Cook rice, 1/2 the amount of time, 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes to chicken and broth and cook for 20 minutes.
Add rice (half cooked) to chicken.
Cook for 20 minutes more or until rice is tender.
Add peas, pimentos and parsley. Cook for 5 minutes.

title: deadly delicious potatoes
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter.
Mix frozen hash brown potatoes, sour cream, cream of chicken soup and Cheddar cheese.
Put in a baking dish.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix per instructions on box. Bake in two 9 x 13-inch floured and greased pans for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°. Cool and remove from pans.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Chop onion and pepper; add to beef and cook until vegetables are done.
Add chili sauce to beef mixture.
Bring to bubble and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Fold in vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (prepared with Pam and flour) at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cool and frost if desired.
Will stay moist and fresh for days.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix together in a large plastic bag and turn frequently for about 2 hours.
Do not bake!

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles until tender, drain;
Rinse noodles in cold water;
drain.
Mix all together and add zesty Italian dressing. Leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or sheet cake pan.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves the sides of the bowl.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Beat milk and lemon juice.
Drain pineapple juice.
Add to milk mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Stir margarine into spaghetti; add Parmesan cheese and egg whites; form mixture into Pam sprayed 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom.
Cook turkey, onion and pepper; drain. Add spaghetti sauce.
Put over cottage cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put 2 tablespoons of oil in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Set skillet in oven to heat while mixing other ingredients.
Corn may be chopped briefly in food processor. Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into well heated frying pan.
Bake for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: spinach salad
directions: Arrange spinach and mushrooms on 4 plates.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Drizzle over salad.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine, pour into dish (9 x 9-inch).
Stir together sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour over margarine.
Pour fruit over mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk; blend well.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Reduce heat and cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and fruit cocktail; blend well.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugars, then add eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Then mix flour, soda and salt.
Add chips last.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crunchy oriental salad
directions: Crush noodles and brown lightly in butter and cashews.
Chop broccoli well and lightly stem; cool completely.
Drain cashews and noodles on paper towels.
Combine vegetable oil, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Blend well, pour over salad mixture. Toss.
Serve immediately.

title: rolled fish fillets with lemon sauce(appetizer or entree)
directions: Make sauce first and keep it hot.
Melt butter, stir in flour. Add cream and fish stock gradually, stirring constantly.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Bring to boil while stirring.
Remove from heat and continue stirring until sauce is thick and smooth.
Season with salt and pepper; add lemon juice.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in a large bowl on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is melted.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts. Spread in foil lined square pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter 8 x 8-inch pan.
Simmer butter or margarine, milk, sugar and salt for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring until melted and smooth.

title: barbecue steaks
directions: In small bowl combine sauce ingredients and mix well.
Reserve 1/2 cup to serve as sauce.
Place beef steak on grid over ash-covered medium coals.
Grill 12 to 16 minutes for medium-rare to medium doneness, turning once.
Brush both sides of steaks; cut into slices and serve with reserved sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: I cube and cook the sweet potatoes like I'm making boiled potatoes.
When tender, drain off the water and place the potatoes in a bowl.
Add the salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons butter.
Whip this until mashed.
Stir in the marshmallows.
Chill.
Shape into balls, tablespoon size or up to 1/4 cup size.
(When I take this to family gatherings, I make tablespoon size so all can get a portion, 1/4 cup if it's a smaller gathering.)
After shaping, roll the balls into the chopped pecans and place in a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Heat the 1 1/3 cups honey and 1 tablespoon butter in the microwave for 2 minutes on High or until bubbling. Pour over the sweet potatoes and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, covered.
The sweet potato mixture freezes well.
You can cook down a desired amount of potatoes, mixed with equal amount of ingredients up to the marshmallows and place in freezer bags with the right amount of ingredients for this recipe.
When needed, get out a package, defrost and microwave to heat it up.
Then continue on with the pecans and honey mixture and bake.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add nuts.
Stir well.
Microwave 4 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and cook 1 minute longer.
Add soda and quickly stir until light and foamy.
Pour on buttered dish adn spread to a thin layer.
You have to work fast.
When cool break into pieces.

title: zook's puffers(ham and cheese puffs)
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
Grease a large cookie sheet. In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat water and butter until butter melts and mixture boils.
Remove saucepan from
heat. With a wooden spoon, vigorously stir in flour and mustard
all at
once
until mixture forms a ball, and leaves sides of pan. Preheat oven to 375°.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition until mixture is smooth; beat in
ham
and
cheese (cheese
does
not
need to melt).
Drop batter,
using
a
large spoon
and
pushing
off with rubber spatula,
onto
prepared cookie sheet into 12 mounds, about 2 inches
apart, swirling top of each.
Bake 35 minutes or until golden.
Serve
as
bread
with soup,
salad
or main course. They're
great with tomato soup! Makes 12 puffs; 145 calories per puff.

title: german cabbage
directions: Saute cabbage and onions in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: chili
directions: Bring all ingredients, except kidney beans, to a boil and then simmer for 20 minutes.
Add kidney beans and cook for 10 minutes more.
When serving in bowls, sprinkle chopped Monterey Jack cheese, chopped onion and sour cream on top.

title: saucy baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot fat. Season with salt and pepper. Drain off excess fat. Mix remaining ingredients; add to pork chops. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs(in the microwave)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on safe rack and cook covered for 6 minutes on Full power or until done.
Drain fat.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a food processor.
Place in a baking dish and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until the whole house smells divine.

title: quick and easy chocolate brownie pie
directions: Prepare the brownie mix as directed on the box.
Spread the brownie mixture over the prepared pie shell evenly.
Top with whole pecans evenly over the top.
Bake until crust is golden brown and a wooden pick inserted in the center of the pie comes out clean, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm and, if desired, with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: yum yum coffee cake
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the sour cream, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
Stir in the vanilla.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix oil and milk together and add to flour.
Mix well and shape into ball.
Place between wax paper and roll out with a rolling pin.
Line pie dish and stick with a fork.
Makes enough for 2 small pies.

title: betty's spanish bean and sausage stew
directions: Soak beans 6 to 8 hours or overnight at room temperature in a large deep pot covered with 2 inches of cold water.
Drain beans into colander; dry the pot.
Heat oil in same pot over medium heat.
Saute onion, bacon and garlic until onion is wilted.
Cut ham into 1 inch pieces; add to beans, 5 cups water, chorizo, paprika, parsley and bay leaves.
Bring to boil; cover.
Reduce heat; simmer 45 minutes.
Add tomato, cumin, salt and pepper. Cook 15 to 25 minutes more or until beans are tender.
Skim fat. Remove from heat and let stand covered 5 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 8 dinner servings.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix all the above together except coconut.
After mixing well, separate into four to six parts.
Roll out in long rolls, then roll in coconut.
Wrap rolls in wax paper; place in freezer several days.
This helps blend all the flavor together and soften the graham crackers.
When removed from freezer, let thaw; slice 1/2-inch slices.
This will keep in freezer several months.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add milk.
Cook 15 minutes or until thick.
Add egg yolks and cook about 5 minutes longer.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Pour in cooled, baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.
Bake in slow oven until lightly browned.

title: cheerios snack mix
directions: Put the Cheerios, peanuts and raisins in a large brown paper bag.
Bring the brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt to a boil in a microwave dish; boil for 2 minutes.
Stir in the baking soda. Pour this mixture into the bag; shake and microwave for 1-1/2 minutes.
Shake again and microwave another 1-1/2 minutes.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet and stir as it cools.
Add M&M's when cool.
This makes about 3/4 of a 5 quart ice cream pail.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and shape into one large ball (or two small balls).
Cover with chopped nuts.

title: baked tuna
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate cheese ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing with blender.
Divide mixture in half and roll in pecans to coat.
Cover and chill for 5 hours or until ready to serve.
Pull vegetable peeler down candy bar to garnish cheese before serving on gingersnaps.

title: pecan-chocolate chip pie
directions: Spread chocolate pieces in unbaked pie shell; freeze at least 1 hour.
Using mixer at medium speed, beat together corn syrup, sugar, melted butter, eggs and salt until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour over the frozen chocolate pieces in pie shell.
Bake at
for
50 minutes or until filling sets. Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Take 3 cups water and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil one minute.
Then add dry jello, strawberry drink and 6 quarts of water. Put in freezer until frozen, then chop up good, it
will be a slush.

title: cardinal punch
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Makes a lovely bright red punch for the Christmas holiday or Valentine's day.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries (crushed). Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, mashed bananas and nuts.
Put one-half of mixture in a mold or 8 x 8-inch pan and let set until firm.
Spoon over and spread sour cream.
Carefully add the other 1/2 of the jello mixture and chill.

title: oatmeal butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients together, then fold in oatmeal and butterscotch morsels.
Put mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes (no longer).

title: hawaiian meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef with onion.
Shape into small balls.
Brown meat balls in skillet.
Melt jelly in saucepan and stir in chili sauce.
Add meat balls and simmer 1 hour.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables (drained) in a large glass bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Cool slightly; pour over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: plum cake
directions: Place all the ingredients into mixing bowl and beat approximately 5 minutes. Fold in 1 cup nuts.
Bake in Bundt or tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shish kabob marinade(for 15)
directions: Put vermouth in container.
Add 3 tablespoons beef bouillon. Mix with 1 or 2 cups hot water. Add oil and other spices, then add meat.
Press meat down into liquid so all meat is covered.
Put in refrigerator until liquid is absorbed, overnight at least.
Freeze until ready to cook.

title: hidden valley ranch party pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, salad dressing mix and green onions together.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over the top.
Roll up and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Chill for 2 hours. Cut off roll ends.
Cut rolls into 1 inch slices.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water by directions on package. Spread broccoli in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken pieces on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter in saucepan; brown slightly.
Sprinkle crumbs over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until heated well. Serves 6.

title: chile relleno casserole
directions: In a skillet brown beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Sprinkle meat with the first 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.
Place half half the chilies in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with meat mixture. Arrange remaining chiles over meat.

title: goulash
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in a small amount of oil. Brown hamburger and drain; add to first 3 ingredients. Add peas, tomatoes and cooked macaroni. Simmer together for a few minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix first three ingredients well.
Melt oleo in baking pan. Roll out dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cutter and place in pan over melted oleo.
Bake at 350° to 375° until brown.
Brush tops with oleo.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of blender; process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
May be stored in freezer.
Yields about 1 1/4 cups, same as 14 ounce can.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heavily grease and flour 3 small aluminum loaf pans.
Mix everything together except for nuts and raisins until smooth.
Add nuts and raisins.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool for 2 or 3 minutes, then wrap in foil upside down.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: heath bar cake
directions: First, place the candy bars in the freezer.
Bake the cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While warm, poke several holes throughout the cake with a large fork.
Pour butterscotch and chocolate topping over the cake slowly so they pour into the holes.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Spread container of Cool Whip over top of cake. Break up frozen candy bars into tiny pieces and garnish the Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal cookies(shaped)
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Add shortening (part margarine), egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Mix and form into balls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: low-fat dressing
directions: Pinch bread up in a bowl.
Pour in broth, onions, sage, salt and pepper.
Add Egg Beaters; stir up well.
Put in 8 x 10-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions; drain and set aside.
Cook mixed vegetables; drain and set aside.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Eat with crackers.

title: bob's favorite chip dip
directions: Beat with mixer until mixed together.
Great with chips.

title: hawaiian luau bites
directions: Drain water chestnuts and cut in half.
Marinate in soy sauce and brown sugar for 4 hours.
Cut bacon strips in thirds; secure with toothpicks.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until bacon is crisp, about 25 minutes.

title: southwestern stir-fry
directions: Combine sherry, cornstarch, cumin, garlic and salt in a medium bowl.
Add pork slices; stir to coat.
Heat oil over medium-high heat in heavy skillet.
Add pork mixture; stir-fry about 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover pan; simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve hot with chili salsa, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan the coconut and nuts.
Mix cake mix according to box directions.
Pour over coconut and nuts. Melt margarine.
Add cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Stir until all mixed.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, 1/2 cup chopped, cooked onion, 1/4 cup salsa and 1/4 cup Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Set aside.
Heat tortillas in microwave to soften.
Place 3 tablespoons chicken filling in the center of each tortilla and roll; arrange seam side down in shallow ovenproof baking dish.
Set aside.

title: peggy's salad
directions: Tear up lettuce, chop onion and tear off the ends of the broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Mix all of these together with the bacon.
Do not add dressing until time to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with bananas, blending well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: nut-filled baked apples
directions: Wash and core apples.
Do not peel.
In saucepan, combine sugar, water and butter.
Heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. For filling, thoroughly combine Pecan Meal, brown sugar, cinnamon and egg.
Place apples in baking dish and spoon filling into apples until 2/3 full.
Pour syrup over the filling until cavity is filled.
Then pour 1/2 cup water around apples in baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: orange sherbet gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sherbet and mix well. When partially set, add mandarin oranges and fold in whipped cream.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine sugar and corn syrup; cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts; cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and butter; cook on High 1 minute.
Stir in baking soda.
Continue stirring until foamy and light in color. Pour quickly onto lightly buttered cookie sheet; let cool completely.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except walnuts in a large mixing bowl. Stir until well blended.
Shape into a round ball.
Put in refrigerator until firm. Roll ball over crushed nuts until evenly coated.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Toss vegetables and sugar together.
Combine oil, vinegar, celery seed and mustard.
Heat to boiling stage and while hot, pout over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.
Will keep several days.

title: ranch style lentils
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Cook 2 cups of lentils in 5 cups water gently for 20 to 30 minutes with 2 teaspoons salt.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix brown sugar into thawed out ground beef well.
Now brown ground beef in a pan; add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain and remove the ground beef; keep the drippings in pan.
Now cook the cabbage in the drippings until transparent.
Remove; drain. Sprinkle flour on the cabbage.
Keep some of the drippings in pan. Put ginger root into pan; let simmer in drippings for a few seconds to flavor.
Put celery and onions in and cook until a little tender; drain.
Now mix all ingredients together (bean sprouts optional).

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine onion-mushroom soup mix with bread crumbs.
Dip chicken in mixture, coating well.
Lightly grease shallow baking pan; arrange chicken, then drizzle with margarine.
Bake, turning once, 10 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Sprinkle both sides of chops with 1 teaspoon salt.
Heat oil; brown chops on both sides.
Remove.
Saute onion and pepper until softened.
Add tomato and Worcestershire sauces.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer about 2 minutes.
Arrange potatoes in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Pour half of sauce over the potatoes.
Add chops and remaining sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover; bake another 25 minutes.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend well until sugar dissolves.
Make dressing ahead of time so flavors can blend.
Pour dressing just before serving.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Slice dough into 15 to 20 slices, put into a greased Bundt pan, sprinkle pudding over the dough, melt butter and mix sugar and nuts together, pour over dough.
Cover and let rise overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach pickles
directions: Let all but peaches boil 10 minutes.
Drop peaches in syrup and cook until you can pierce them with a fork.
Fill sterilized jars with peaches and pour hot syrup over them; seal.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: In large skillet, brown ground round, onion and garlic. Cook spinach according to package directions; reserve drained spinach liquid and add water to make 1 cup.
Add cheese, bread crumbs, eggs,
oil and reserved liquid to spinach.
Set aside. Add tomato sauces
and pepper to meat mix; simmer 10 minutes. Add spinach mix to meat sauce and stir in noodles.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30
minutes.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet and saute onions, celery and parsley. Pour over bread crumbs in a large bowl.
Add all seasonings and toss together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add soup and mix.
Pack lightly into greased crock-pot.
Cover and set on high for 45 minutes, then reduce setting to low and cook for 4 to 8 hours.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Stir pineapple into sugar and flour mixture. Place in casserole dish.
Put cheese on top of pineapple mixture.
Pour 1/3 to 1/2 cup pineapple juice over cheese. Crumble Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top of pineapple mixture. Dribble butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry supreme
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 8-inch pan. Combine cranberries, sugar and water. Bring to a boil; simmer 20 minutes, until cranberries pop. Stir in nuts and marmalade. Chill. Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, milk and vanilla, mixing until well blended. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon over crust. Top with cranberry mixture. Chill overnight.

title: zucchini and carrot spaghetti
directions: Cut carrots, zucchini and chicken into 5 x 1/2-inch strips. Combine chicken broth and margarine in a large skillet.
Place over medium heat and bring to a boil; add carrots.
Reduce heat and simmer three minutes.
Add zucchini and continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
Drain vegetables and set aside.
Cook spaghetti according to package, omitting salt.
Drain spaghetti and combine with vegetables and chicken.
Serve.
Yields 10 servings. Contains 75 calories, 3 grams protein, 12 grams carbohydrate, 2 grams fat, 2 mg. cholesterol and 118 mg. sodium.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix everything together.
Serve with chips, crackers or vegetables.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Put brown sugar in a large microwave-safe bowl. Pour whipping cream over this. Do not stir. Microwave on High 14 minutes. Remove and add remaining ingredients. Stir together and drop by spoonfuls onto foil.

title: parmesan chicken strips
directions: Trim excess fat from chicken.
Cut chicken into 4 x 1-inch strips.
Combine egg and milk, stirring well.
Combine breadcrumbs and next 5 ingredients; stir well.
Dip chicken strips in egg mixture; dredge in breadcrumb mixture.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 12 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix oleo with corn flakes.
Mix soup, milk and mayonnaise together.
Layer half of the corn flakes, cabbage and half the water chestnuts in baking dish.
Repeat with rest of halves.
Pour soup over all and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beefy beans
directions: In large skillet, combine ground beef, onion and celery. After cooking, drain well.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in shortening until onion is yellow.
Add meat and fry until mixture falls apart.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour, removing cover last 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Best served hot.

title: harvey house slaw
directions: In large bowl make layers of cabbage, green pepper and onion. Sprinkle 1 cup sugar on top.
In saucepan combine mustard, 2 teaspoons sugar, celery seed, salt, vinegar and oil.
Mix well. Bring to full boil, stirring.
Pour over slaw.
Refrigerate covered at least 4 hours or overnight.
To serve, toss.
Serves 8.

title: skor cake
directions: Bake cake
according
to directions in 13 x 9-inch pan. While still warm, poke holes (with wooden spoon handle) in top of cake. Pour
milk over top of cake.
Then pour caramel over top of cake. Refrigerate overnight.

title: boiled brussels sprouts
directions: Remove wilted leaves and let stand about 30 minutes, head down, in cold salted water (1 teaspoon to 1 quart) to draw out insects; wash well.
Cook, uncovered, in large amount of boiling water 10 to 15 minutes, or until just tender.
Drain, season and serve as desired.
Allow 1 quart (1 1/4 to 1 1/2 pounds) for 6 portions.

title: easy rolls
directions: Place water in bowl; add salt.
Mix yeast into dry cake mix and add to water mixture.
Add flour and mix; knead until smooth. Cover and let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Shape into rolls and let stand until double in size.
Bake in preheated 450° oven about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar, corn, salt and butter.
Mix well.
Add well beaten eggs and milk.
Pour into oblong baking dish.
Bake slowly 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven or until done.
Stir well every 5 to 8 minutes.
This should be custard consistency.

title: baked ham
