directions: Combine cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, Coke, brown sugar, allspice and pineapple juice in a pot and bring to a light boil.
Turn fire off when boil begins.
Trim fat and skim from ham.
Make shallow cuts on top of ham about 1 inch apart, forming a diamond or square.
Place ham in baking pan and pour hot mixture on it. Place in 350° oven.
When mixture begins to simmer, begin basting the ham with the juices.
Continue to do this every 15 minutes for approximately every 2 hours.

title: vegetarian derma
directions: You will need aluminum foil for casing.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix together but do not heat.
Spread on bun halves.
Heat under the broiler until cheese bubbles and is golden brown.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain the beans.
Add the chopped onion, celery and green pepper.
Heat the vinegar, sugar, pepper and salt.
Cool and add oil.
Pour over bean mixture.
Let stand 1 hour and serve.

title: egg salad dip
directions: Peel and cut eggs in small pieces.
Mix rest of ingredients and mix well.
Use a little juice from pickle so dip is not too thick.
Serve with crackers or small rye bread.

title: orange chocolate chip muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper. Finely grate orange peel.
Beat sugar and butter in large bowl until pale and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add orange peel, orange juice and yogurt.
Mix well. Mix dry ingredients together and sprinkle over batter, folding gently just
enough to blend.
Spoon into muffin cups and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown and top springs back if lightly touched.
Cool on rack.

title: chili meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce with brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, chili powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt in saucepan. Cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Combine ground beef, milk, oats, onion and remaining salt and pepper; mix well.
Add half the sauce to beef mixture; blend well.
Press beef mixture into ungreased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan; spoon remaining sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fish italiano
directions: Pat fish dry.
Combine cereal, Parmesan cheese, parsley, garlic powder, paprika, salt and pepper in a shallow dish, mixing well.
Dip fish in egg whites and then in crumb mixture, coating well.
Arrange in a shallow 2-quart baking dish, with thickest portions to the outside of the dish.
Cover with plastic wrap, venting to allow steam to escape and microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork, turning the dish every 2 minutes.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Serves 4.
(Other fish could be used.)

title: holiday breakfast pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Crumble bacon on bottom evenly.
Layer cheese, then onion.
Mix all other ingredients; pour over onion. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Wait 5 minutes before cutting. This recipe can be prepared the night before and stored in the refrigerator.
Bake the next morning.

title: tropical blender smoothie
directions: Blend until smooth. Store extra in an air-tight container. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and soft margarine together.
Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes; cool for 1 hour.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together, then spread mixture over cooled crust.
Dissolve strawberry jello in water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir well.
Chill slightly. Pour over other layer.
Chill until well set.
Garnish with crushed pretzels.

title: dutch cake or cracker pudding
directions: Crush crackers; set aside.
Scald milk over moderate heat or in double boiler.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add milk slowly to egg yolks, stirring well.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in 1/2 cup sugar and cook, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes.
Add cracker crumbs.
Pour into buttered 7 x 11-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until they hold peaks.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar.
Spread over mixture in baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven until top is golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: hot cheese puffs
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine cheese and butter or margarine. Cook and stir over low heat.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Fold cheese mixture into egg whites.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix the pecans and coconut together; pour into greased sheet pan.
Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut in pan.
Cream the cream cheese and margarine.
Add the 4x sugar.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool in pan.

title: cranberry jello salad #1
directions: In blender, grind cranberries and peeled oranges.
Pour sugar over them and let sit.
Make jello as per instructions on box (you could use 1/4 - 1/2 cup less water).
Combine jello and fruit mixture.
Grease mold or bowl or glass pan with salad oil or mayonnaise and then pour mixture in.
Chill until it is set.

title: spaghetti with garlic and oil
directions: In small saucepan or skillet, cook garlic in olive oil until golden brown.
Stir in parsley, salt, red pepper and pepper.
Heat and stir for 3 minutes.
Toss garlic mixture with spaghetti or other pasta until coated.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings. Make your favorite tossed salad and garlic bread.
Have some wine too.
Enjoy!

title: kabobs
directions: Marinate meat overnight. Drain and place on skewers in any order.
Approximate amounts per skewer:
4 pieces red pepper, 4 pieces green pepper, 4 pieces meat, 2 pieces pineapple and 1 mushroom.
Grill over low flame, basting often with soy sauce.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake(phelps sauerkraut festival)
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder and set aside.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, salt and cocoa.
Mix well.
Alternate flour and water; add kraut.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: welke's white cookies
directions: Combine ingredients as listed, adding flour 1 cup at a time until you have a stiff dough.
(Dough doesn't stick when you press it.)
On a floured surface roll out dough to around 3/8 to 1/2-inch thick.
Place cut out cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet.
(We usually use a 3-inch round one and place a raisin in the center. Also before cutting shapes out, you may sprinkle the dough with sugar.)
Bake until just done, not brown in 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix both soups together.
Boil chicken until done.
Add chicken broth to soup mixture.
Cool chicken enough to bone.
Add chicken pieces to soup mixture.
Add 4 cups cooked rice.
Add 1 cup shredded Velveeta.
Add garlic salt.
Stir.
Microwave for 10 minutes or bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion and beef in skillet and drain off fat. Combine this with rest of the ingredients. Place in greased casserole. Beat egg into mashed potatoes; spoon in mounds over top. Sprinkle cheese over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake with caramel sauce
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together; add eggs and dry ingredients.
Then blend in apples and walnuts.
Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken tasty and tangy
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken in small saucepan.
Heat on low until butter is melted and ingredients are blended.
Dip each piece of chicken in sauce and place skin side down in a shallow baking pan.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Then turn pieces skin side up.
Bake 35 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: favorite chocolate pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Mix next 6 ingredients well in blender. Melt oleo in a large, heavy saucepan.
Add the blended ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until well thickened.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool.
Cover with Cool Whip and chill well (for low-fat use Lite Cool Whip).

title: crab mousse
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Heat soup.
Add gelatine to 1/4 cup cold water; when softened, mix with heated soup.
Add everything but the crab to the soup mix; mix well and then add crabmeat (drained).
Spray jello mold with Pam and add the mixture. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving with your crackers of choice.

title: sunday pot roast
directions: Late Saturday night, place all ingredients in crock-pot with 1 cup water.
Cook on low.
When you come home from church, dinner is waiting for you.

title: cretons
directions: Cover meat with water, cook 2 hours.
Add crackers (crushed). Put in small dishes, let set.

title: easy etouffee
directions: Saute onion, bell peppers, celery, garlic, and butter. Add shrimp and tomatoes. Cook for 30 minutes, serve over rice.

title: thank you cake
directions: Mix cake mix (only), 2 eggs and vanilla pudding together in bowl.
Pour into oblong baking dish.
Top with chips and nuts. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: salata (tossed salad)
directions: Cut vegetables as desired.
Add lemon juice and oil and toss.

title: grandmom hagan's jewish apple pie
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Peel and slice 4 or 5 medium apples.
Mix apples with 1/2 cup of sugar and 3 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Set aside.
Put dry ingredients in a bowl. Make a hole; pour in oil, orange juice and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat at medium speed.
Add 1/2 the batter to tube pan, then a layer of apples.
Pour the rest of the batter, then apples on top of that.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and juice.
Beat 2 minutes and spoon over batter.
Leave 2-inches around sides.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage; stir flour in melted butter.
Take off heat.
Mix rest of ingredients and add cheese.
Cook until thick.
This is best served hot.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix margarine and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla, nuts and flour.
Pour in long, greased pan.
Cook at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut while hot.
Let cool in pan.

title: salsa
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve with taco chips.

title: strawberry-fig preserves
directions: After removing the stem from figs, cut figs into small pieces. May use an electric beater for a finer texture.
Add jello and sugar to the figs.
Cook slowly over low fire while stirring constantly.
Once it reaches boiling point, continue to cook for 3 or 4 minutes.
Mixture should be poured into hot jars.
If not place in refrigerator after cooling, seal with paraffin and store on shelf.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the melted margarine.
Add flour, one cup at a time, and mix.
Add anise flavoring to suit your taste.
Spoon mixture on pizelle iron and cook until golden brown.

title: oven roasted veggies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl or plastic bag.
Shake until coated. Empty contents onto a large baking sheet and bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until tender, stirring once during baking.

title: potato casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes, onions and English peas
in layers in 1 1/2-quart casserole
dish.	Mix soup and milk together.
Add soup and milk
mixtures	to
casserole.	Chip butter over top. Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions in butter and olive oil until clear but not brown.
Add the meat and saute until well done.
Add tomato sauce, paste and wine.
Cook for a few minutes until well mixed.
Add the remaining ingredients, cover and cook slowly 45 minutes to 1 hour. Add beans if desired.
Serves about 6.

title: freezer cucumber pickles
directions: Thinly slice cucumbers and onion.
Mix with salt.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Drain; press out as much juice as you can, but do not rinse.
Mix white vinegar with sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cucumber-onion mixture.
Place cucumbers in small freezer containers or bags.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: raspberry impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put raspberries in pie pan.
Blend eggs, sugar, milk, Bisquick and butter in blender.
Pour blended mixture over raspberries in pie pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. (Other fruits may be substituted for raspberries.)

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into graham crust.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken breasts with sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch baking pan or baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover pan with foil and bake 45 minutes in 375° to 400° oven.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes or until set.
May need to place pan of water above pie to keep from getting too brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add taco seasoning; mix until well blended.
Spread in thin layer on serving tray.
Sprinkle with cheese, lettuce and tomato (chopped olives and chopped jalapeno peppers may also be used if desired). Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: fudge cake(brownies)
directions: Melt butter and chocolate (or cocoa) over very low heat.
Add other ingredients except nuts.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in 2 greased 8-inch square cake pans at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon pineapple cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add lemon-lime beverage; mix well. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans, let cool completely.
Spread Pineapple Topping between layers and on top of cake.

title: cantaloupe ice
directions: Place sugar and water in a saucepan and stir them over high heat until the mixture begins to bubble and sugar is dissolved. Simmer 5 minutes.
Place in a jar and refrigerate until cool. Peel and seed the cantaloupe; cut into cubes.
Puree in a blender or food processor (this should make 3 1/2 cups puree).
Add lemon juice and syrup.
Freeze in a machine according to directions, or freeze in trays 30 minutes before serving, blend or process again. Put back in the freezer to firm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange-mint punch
directions: Stir sugar and water in saucepan; simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over mint leaves to steep.
Strain after 2 hours.
Combine minted syrup with all ingredients except ginger ale.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs, sugar, oleo and peanut butter. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate overnight.
In top of double boiler, place wax and chocolate bits; don't let water boil in bottom of pan.
Stir until chocolate chips and wax are melted.
Dip balls into chocolate.
Place on wax paper to harden.
Roll into nuts or coconut if desired after dipping.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine pecans and coconut and sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour cake mix over pecans and coconut.

title: apricot-pineapple salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, crushed pineapple and sugar.
Cook until it simmers. Add apricot baby food and cream cheese.
Mix well and cool.

title: jello shooters
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Stir well; add cold water and vodka in strength you want.
Pour into 1-ounce souffle cups and refrigerate.
Good for party or outing.
You can get the 1-ounce cups at craft stores or Redmonds.

title: ah-me's cabbage casserole
directions: Spread corn flake crumbs in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over top of crumbs.
Cut up cabbage and onions, enough to fill dish.
Pour a can of cream of celery soup (with a little milk mixed in) over top of cabbage.
Top with more corn flake crumbs and melted butter.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Add sugar, eggs and margarine.
Beat well.
Add bananas and mix until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to complete cooling.

title: rice krispies marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Using a buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, coated with cooking spray.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yields twenty-four 2 x 2-inch treats.

title: baskin-robbins pie
directions: Mix oleo, flour and pecans thoroughly and spread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown; let cool.
Mix thoroughly the cream cheese and sugar. Add 1/2 of the carton of Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread on crust.
Beat at low speed the vanilla and chocolate pudding with the milk until thick.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and maraschino cherries for garnish.
Chill and serve.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until fluffy.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Spread in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: You can either boil the chicken breasts (I usually boil them and then cut into chunks). You can chunk them and saute in small amount of butter. Saute onion and garlic in butter, then add the next 9 ingredients. Mix chicken and the rest of ingredients and simmer for 1 hour. Serve with Monterey Jack cheese sprinkled on top. Serve with Doritos chips.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer pie filling and pineapple.
Next, take the yellow cake mix (dry) and sprinkle over cherries and pineapple.
Pour melted butter over cake.
Add coconut and pecans, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: greenfield village chocolate chip cookies(100-year-old recipe)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, flour, salt, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: marinated veggies
directions: Peel and cut carrots into sticks.
Tear broccoli into pieces. Combine all ingredients and marinate overnight.
Garnish with parsley.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.

title: moist one layer chocolate cake
directions: Melt margarine, add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar (beat) then flour, 1/2 cup oil, buttermilk, and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into oblong baking pan and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk, shortening, egg and vanilla to the mixture and mix into a smooth dough.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cheese stuffed baked tomatoes
directions: Cut a slice from top of tomatoes and remove seeds and some pulp to leave a shell.
Do not peel.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Cook onions and celery in oil until tender.
Add rice, cheese, milk, salt, and pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Pile filling into shells and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 400° until crumbs are browned (about 10 to 12 minutes). Do not overcook.
Serve immediately.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend dry ingredients. Cut in shortening until consistency of small peas. Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time. Roll thin on well floured surface. Line greased pans with dough. Makes 2 crusts.

title: taco salad(in oblong dish)
directions: Layer 1/2 bag tortilla chips, grated cheese, chili and sour cream in dish.
Put on other half of bag of tortilla chips.
Put more grated cheese over this.
Heat in microwave oven until cheese is melted.
Add chopped tomatoes, chopped green onions and chopped lettuce on top of taco salad.

title: elaine's stained glass candy
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until 310° on candy thermometer. Add the oil base food flavoring and food coloring.
Pour onto cookie sheet. When cool and hardened, chop into pieces and dust with powdered sugar.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in 2-quart casserole (13 x 9-inch pan). Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip-oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugars and vanilla together until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats and chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Whip together and add meat.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish.
Slivered almonds on top are optional.
Serve with crackers.

title: dixie lily party rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar and set aside.
Measure shortening and remaining sugar in a large mixing bowl. Add 2 cups boiling water.
Mix and cool to lukewarm. Beat in eggs and yeast.
Stir in enough more flour to make a soft dough. Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in oleo until tender, not brown.
Mix eggs, soup, salt, pepper, Worcestershire, curry powder and mustard.
Crumble crackers into this mixture.
Add sauteed vegetables and hamburger meat.
Blend well with hands. Pile into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove from oven and drain off juices and fat.
Cover with catsup and bake 15 minutes more.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: About 1 hour before serving or early in the day:

In a medium bowl with wire whisk or fork, mix carrots, yogurt, egg substitute, applesauce, raisins, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended. With spoon, stir flour mixture into carrot mixture just until flour is moistened. Spoon batter into 6 ounce brioche pans or jumbo muffin pan cups which have been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center of each muffin comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pans. Cool slightly on wire racks. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
For every muffin cup, use 1 pat of batter.
Let melt.
Spoon in dough about 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hurry up dessert
directions: Put can of pie mix in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cut butter in about 24 pieces and dot over nuts or melt butter and drizzle on top.
Place in preheated oven at 350° or 35 minutes.

title: peach tea
directions: Mix and store in a container with a tight lid.
Place 2 teaspoons in cup of boiling water.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, spread sauerkraut, crumbled corned beef and cheese.
Spoon dressing over cheese; plate tomatoes on top.
Mix caraway seed, cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Place over tomatoes; bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Can be made and refrigerated hours before baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well and chill!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed; make the size of a walnut and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: diabetic fruit pie
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil. Let cook then pour into pie crust cover with a pie crust and Bake at 425 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: sweet yeast dough for cinnamon rolls or coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening to hot milk.
Cool to lukewarm, then beat in eggs.
Add two cups flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Cover with bowl and let rest 10 minutes. Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and lightly grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Punch down and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into rolls, coffee cakes or tea rings.
Place on greased pans and lightly brush tops with oil. Cover lightly with wax paper and let rise in a warm place.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes for coffee cake; 20 to 25 minutes for pan rolls.

title: taffy apple cookies
directions: You will also need spray Pam, midget size baking cups and toothpicks.

title: dilled meatballs
directions: Mix beef, oats, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon dill weed. Form into evenly shaped 1-inch meatballs.
In hot oil, cook a few at a time until well browned; remove to large bowl.
Pour off oil and return meatballs to skillet.
Stir in soup mix and water. Over medium heat, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in sour cream and 2 teaspoons dill weed; heat through on low.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: mother's apple relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Seal in sterilized jars.
Use Red Delicious apples.

title: texas gold bars
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
After mixing, this will look like cookie dough.
Press into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve both jellos in boiling water.
Add, mixing with whisk, remaining ingredients.
Mix well and jell in refrigerator. Keeps for several days.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients, then add next 9 ingredients.
Pour in large baking dish.
Add last 3 ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease long cake pan, then spread coconut and nuts in bottom of cake pan.
Set aside.
Mix cake mix up by using recipe on box. Pour over coconut and nut mixture.
Then, in small bowl, mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Pour this batter over cake mixture.

title: pepper steak
directions: Marinate beef strips with soy sauce and black pepper for at least 6 hours.
In a wok, heat oil until hot.
Add onions, meat and cook for 3 minutes.
Add plum and hoisin sauces and sugar.
Cover and cook for 3 minutes; add green pepper.
Mix cold water and cornstarch.
Add to the mixture; stir to evenly thicken sauce. Serve over rice.

title: carrot cheese bake
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots in sugar water; drain. Put carrots in greaaed 6 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Melt cheese and margarine and pour over carrots.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tomato and asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut
stem
ends off tomatoes and slice into 3 thick slices.
Cut
asparagus
spears in half and arrange on top of tomato slices
in a shallow buttered 2 quart rectangular baking dish.
Combine
remaining
ingredients
and spoon over asparagus and tomatoes.
Bake
for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Do
not
overbake.
Yields
6 to 8 servings.

title: edna's macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 325 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken for 1 hour.
Cook broccoli.
In large bowl, mix cream of mushroom soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and Cheddar cheese.
Layer broccoli and chicken in dish and the mixture over it.
Add the rest of the grated cheese over the top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: instant date nut roll
directions: Mix all together until thoroughly moistened.
Divide in half. Place on a sheet of plastic wrap and roll to form 2 (1 1/2-inch thick) rolls.
Makes 2 rolls about 8-inches long.
Seal ends of plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: pork chop-potato casserole
directions: Debone and trim fat from pork chops.
Beat flour, add salt and pepper and fry until brown.
While pork chops are frying, precook potatoes by boiling on top of stove.
Add soup and water in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add onion soup.
Put potatoes in soup mixture and place pork chops on top.
Cover with foil, bake until soup bubbles (about 30 to 45 minutes).

title: candy (fairy food)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and vinegar.
Boil to 310° in big kettle. Remove from heat and cool until bubbling stops.
Mix in vanilla and baking soda.
Cool in 9 x 12-inch pan, buttered.
Remove from pan; break in chunks and dip in melted chocolate.

title: super bowl cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Pour Eagle Brand evenly over crust.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients in order listed. Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Blend in flour and bouillon.
Add milk and corn.
Stir until thick.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: glazed ham
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ham.
Pour mixture over ham and bake at 300° for 2 hours, basting.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, place all ingredients.
Close and shake until potatoes are well coated.
Put potatoes in shallow baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes stirring occasionally or until potatoes are tender.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Sift in flour, soda and tartar. Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
These will flatten as they bake, so space well on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 dozen large cookies.

title: spinach-potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes, drain and peel.
Add butter and mash until smooth.
Add sour cream and seasonings, mix well.
Add cooked and well drained spinach, mix well.
Place in casserole dish with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add water and vanilla and mix well. Add flour and pecans; chill 3 or 4 hours.
Shape into balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven, 325°, about 18 to 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.
Let cool and roll again.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: out of this world rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Let stand 10 minutes. Combine dissolved yeast, eggs, 2 1/2 cups flour, 1 cup warm water, shortening, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth about 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl often with wooden spoon.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down, refrigerate overnight.
Three hours before baking, divide dough in half.
Roll out each half into a rectangle.
Spread with butter. Cut out shape as desired.
Place in a greased baking pan.
Cover and let rise 3 hours until double.
Bake at 400° 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and spices.
Add pumpkin and eggs; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 35 minutes or until custard is set.

title: gourmet snack
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand 30 minutes and then store in tightly covered tin.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in loaf pan.
Pour 1 can tomato soup over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with mustard sauce.
Serves 6.

title: cheese-chive butter
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Makes 2/3 cup.
Spread on loaf.
Wrap in foil.
Heat in oven.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine corn, cooked broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup crushed crackers, onion, butter, salt and pepper.
Pour in casserole.
Top with 1/4 cup of crushed saltines mixed with 1 tablespoon of butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients.
Butter a casserole dish and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Place 3 pats of butter on top and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat chili 4 minutes in microwave, stirring frequently.
Add Velveeta.
Microwave 2 minutes until melted.
Serve hot with chips.
Reheat in microwave if needed.

title: ham quiche
directions: Put meat in bottom of pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over meat. Bake 1 hour between 325° and 350°.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix all ingredients until a spreadable consistency.

title: sausage and tomatoes
directions: Brown sausage well in oil, then add tomatoes and basil. Simmer 1 hour and serve with Italian bread.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble Oreo cookies; set aside 1 cup of crumbs.
Press the rest of the crumbs in butter to make crust.

title: aunt patty's sour cream cake
directions: Separate flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs.
Alternate flour mixture and sour cream into butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube or sheet pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and knife through. Drizzle some on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for almost one hour.

title: grama squares
directions: With hands, mix ingredients together real well.
Looks like paste.
Spray 11 x 7-inch pan with Pam.
Spread ingredients evenly with hands, corner to corner.
Smooth top with back of spoon. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool completely; cut in squares.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in pot with margarine; do not brown.
Add can of soup, water, milk, rice and broccoli, and pieces of cheese if desired.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy pot pie
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Mix chicken, both soups and drained Veg-All in large bowl.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Combine jam and sour cream.
Add jam mixture alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beating well until combined.
Stir in nuts.
Divide among 5 greased and floured 4 1/2 x 2 3/4 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes in pans; remove and cool completely on wire racks.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: chocolate-rice krispie drops
directions: Melt pieces of
Hershey
bars
over
hot water in large mixing bowl.
Add pecans, Krispies and raisins; mix well until everything is covered with chocolate.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Allow to dry in a cool rooom for several hours.

title: spinach tart
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, adding 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon lemon peel.
Drain, pressing out as much water as possible.
Saute onion in margarine, adding the oregano.
Combine spinach, onion, 1/2 cup sour cream, egg, lemon juice and additional salt to your taste.
Spoon into unbaked pastry shells.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Spoon remaining sour cream over tarts and garnish with ripe olives just before serving.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a large pan over medium heat, saute onion in butter. Reduce heat; stir in flour.
Add warm water slowly.
Add granules and spices.
Bring to a boil by raising heat.
Reduce heat to low. Add broccoli and milk and simmer 10 minutes until broccoli is cooked.
Stir in half and half and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: scrapple mix
directions: Put ingredients in large roaster.
Bake for 2 hours at 250°. Mix well, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread out to cool.

title: peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Stir together dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly by hand. Fold in peaches and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening until fine.
Add milk all at once.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes in muffin pans.

title: tacos in a shell
directions: Cook shells according to directions; drain well and add 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Brown meat and drain.
Cube cream cheese and let melt in meat.
Stir in chili powder.
Stuff shells and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour taco sauce over shells and cover.
Cook 15 minutes and uncover.
Put cheese over shells and cook 15 minutes longer.
(Garnish with tortilla chips and green onions if desired.)

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices in large bowl.
Beat eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil in separate bowl.
Stir into flour mixture just until blended.
Fold in raisins and walnuts.
Spoon into greased muffin tins about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 1 quart covered casserole using 1/2 can of French fried onions in the casserole and 1/2 can sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Make a crust out of melted oleo and graham cracker crumbs; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar with cream cheese; spread on graham crust.
Spread on strawberries and then pineapple and bananas.
Mix pudding, milk, Dream Whip and vanilla together for 3 minutes.
Spread on top.

title: ma maw's apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla, cinnamon and flour. Add apples and nuts. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat, lo-cal layered dessert
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix; cook.
Tear 1/2 cake in bottom of dish or bowl.
Pour 1/2 pudding mixture over cake.
Layer 1/2 fruit, then Cool Whip.
Repeat layers:
cake, pudding, fruit, Cool Whip.
Decorate top with pieces of fruit.

title: banana nut bread
directions: *Sour milk by adding 1 tablespoon vinegar to 5 tablespoons of milk.

title: crab dip
directions: Dice up crab into bowl.
Add eggs and salad dressing to taste. Stir altogether.
Serve on
Club crackers.

title: crunch top sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, whipped topping, powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla in a mixing bowl; beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour mixture into Coconut Crust.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix in the order of ingredients and beat after each addition. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Grease Pyrex dish (pie plate works well) with butter or margarine.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Mix ingredients for topping:
oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: In a frypan, brown spareribs in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil. Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Add spareribs and mixture into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon of the cornstarch into the cooked rhubarb, stirring constantly, over low heat.
Mix remaining sugar, cornstarch, salt, milk and eggs in a double boiler. Cook until it is thickened. Stir in rhubarb mixture to this when both are cooled.
Chill and serve.
Makes 5 servings.
Very good.

title: jambalaya
directions: In
a 6-quart heavy saucepan, melt butter and add diced pork, onions, peppers and bay leaves.
Saute until pork is brown and vegetables are soft.
Add sausage and ham.
Saute briefly.
Add garlic, thyme, cloves, chili powder and tomatoes; cook for 5 minutes, then add rice and chicken stock.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and hot sauce and adjust seasoning.
Continue to cook until rice is done, yet still firm; adjust seasoning again.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: venison steaks with mushrooms and green peppercorn butter
directions: Grind peppercorns and mix with 6 tablespoons butter.
Melt the remaining butter in a large skillet along with the oil and when sizzling, toss in the minced garlic and mushrooms.
Saute over moderate heat, seasoning with salt and pepper and tossing occasionally for about 5 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon and keep warm.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt stick of butter in pan.
Chop up onion, then put in the rice.
Brown.
Put rice and onion mixture in casserole dish.
Then add the beef broth and the jar of mushrooms.
Stir real good. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fast and easy chili
directions: In 12-inch skillet, brown ground beef over medium-high heat, drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer covered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes.
Serve, if desired, over hot cooked rice.

title: strawberry cream
directions: Place cottage cheese in a blender container. Cover and blend until smooth. Add frozen strawberries, ice milk and orange peel. Cover and blend until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides as necessary. Pour strawberry mixture into 4 stemmed glasses and serve at once.
Garnish with a small piece of fresh fruit, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in a covered container.
Use 1/3 cup mix to a cup of boiling water.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, stirring well. Gradually stir in broth, broccoli and bay leaf.
Cook over medium heat until broccoli is tender, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and remove bay leaf.
Add pepper.
Add milk right before serving. Makes 4 to 5 cups.

title: turkey delight
directions: Cook turkey breast; boil 3 cups of broth.
Add chopped onions, peas, celery, potatoes, carrots, cream of chicken soup, sage, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with or over cornbread.

title: tuna chow mein casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir celery, onion and green pepper in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in tuna (with liquid) and remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with reserved chow mein noodles.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
